  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 51ee3e37f5ded7941ab6216610f6fc67, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: A Message for Rebellious Judah
      content: '  These are the visions that Isaiah son of Amoz saw concerning Judah
        and Jerusalem. He saw these visions during the years when Uzziah, Jotham,
        Ahaz, and Hezekiah were kings of Judah.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:1 '
        content: These kings reigned from 792 to 686 <span class="ChapterContent_sc__Hg9da">b.c.</span>
    - title: 
      content: "Listen, O heavens! Pay attention, earth!This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says:\u201CThe children I raised and cared forhave rebelled against me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Even an ox knows its owner,and a donkey recognizes its master\u2019s
        care\u2014but Israel doesn\u2019t know its master.My people don\u2019t recognize
        my care for them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Oh, what a sinful nation they are\u2014loaded down with a burden
        of guilt.They are evil people,corrupt children who have rejected the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.They
        have despised the Holy One of Israeland turned their backs on him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Why do you continue to invite punishment?Must you rebel forever?Your
        head is injured,and your heart is sick.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You are battered from head to foot\u2014covered with bruises, welts,
        and infected wounds\u2014without any soothing ointments or bandages.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your country lies in ruins,and your towns are burned.Foreigners plunder
        your fields before your eyesand destroy everything they see.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Beautiful Jerusalem[[COMMENT(0)]] stands abandonedlike a watchman\u2019s
        shelter in a vineyard,like a lean-to in a cucumber field after the harvest,like
        a helpless city under siege.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:8 '
        content: Hebrew <b>The daughter of Zion.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "If the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armieshad not
        spared a few of us,[[COMMENT(0)]]we would have been wiped out like Sodom,destroyed
        like Gomorrah.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:9 '
        content: Greek version reads <b>a few of our children. </b>Compare Rom 9:29.
    - title: 
      content: "Listen to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, you leaders of \u201CSodom.\u201DListen
        to the law of our God, people of \u201CGomorrah.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhat makes you think I want all your sacrifices?\u201Dsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CI am sick of your burnt offerings of
        ramsand the fat of fattened cattle.I get no pleasure from the bloodof bulls
        and lambs and goats.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When you come to worship me,who asked you to parade through my courts
        with all your ceremony?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Stop bringing me your meaningless gifts;the incense of your offerings
        disgusts me!As for your celebrations of the new moon and the Sabbathand your
        special days for fasting\u2014they are all sinful and false.I want no more
        of your pious meetings.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I hate your new moon celebrations and your annual festivals.They
        are a burden to me. I cannot stand them!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When you lift up your hands in prayer, I will not look.Though you
        offer many prayers, I will not listen,for your hands are covered with the
        blood of innocent victims.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Wash yourselves and be clean!Get your sins out of my sight.Give up
        your evil ways.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Learn to do good.Seek justice.Help the oppressed.Defend the cause
        of orphans.Fight for the rights of widows.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CCome now, let\u2019s settle this,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CThough
        your sins are like scarlet,I will make them as white as snow.Though they
        are red like crimson,I will make them as white as wool.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If you will only obey me,you will have plenty to eat.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Unfaithful Jerusalem
      content: "But if you turn away and refuse to listen,you will be devoured by
        the sword of your enemies.I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have spoken!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'See how Jerusalem, once so faithful,has become a prostitute.Once
        the home of justice and righteousness,she is now filled with murderers.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Once like pure silver,you have become like worthless slag.Once so
        pure,you are now like watered-down wine.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your leaders are rebels,the companions of thieves.All of them love
        bribesand demand payoffs,but they refuse to defend the cause of orphansor
        fight for the rights of widows.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, the Lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies,the Mighty One of Israel, says,\u201CI will take revenge on my enemiesand
        pay back my foes!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will raise my fist against you.I will melt you down and skim off
        your slag.I will remove all your impurities.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then I will give you good judges againand wise counselors like you
        used to have.Then Jerusalem will again be called the Home of Justiceand the
        Faithful City.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Zion will be restored by justice;those who repent will be revived
        by righteousness.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But rebels and sinners will be completely destroyed,and those who
        desert the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will be consumed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will be ashamed of your idol worshipin groves of sacred oaks.You
        will blush because you worshipedin gardens dedicated to idols.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will be like a great tree with withered leaves,like a garden
        without water.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Future Reign"
      content: '  This is a vision that Isaiah son of Amoz saw concerning Judah and
        Jerusalem:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In the last days, the mountain of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        housewill be the highest of all\u2014the most important place on earth.It
        will be raised above the other hills,and people from all over the world will
        stream there to worship.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "People from many nations will come and say,\u201CCome, let us go
        up to the mountain of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,to the house of Jacob\u2019s
        God.There he will teach us his ways,and we will walk in his paths.\u201DFor
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s teaching will go out from Zion;his
        word will go out from Jerusalem.  "
      comments: []
    - title: A Warning of Judgment
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will mediate between nationsand will
        settle international disputes.They will hammer their swords into plowsharesand
        their spears into pruning hooks.Nation will no longer fight against nation,nor
        train for war anymore.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Come, descendants of Jacob,let us walk in the light of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has rejected his people,the descendants
        of Jacob,because they have filled their land with practices from the Eastand
        with sorcerers, as the Philistines do.They have made alliances with pagans.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Israel is full of silver and gold;there is no end to its treasures.Their
        land is full of warhorses;there is no end to its chariots.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their land is full of idols;the people worship things they have madewith
        their own hands.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So now they will be humbled,and all will be brought low\u2014do not
        forgive them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Crawl into caves in the rocks.Hide in the dustfrom the terror of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>and the glory of his majesty.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Human pride will be brought down,and human arrogance will be humbled.Only
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will be exaltedon that day of judgment.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armieshas a
        day of reckoning.He will punish the proud and mightyand bring down everything
        that is exalted.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will cut down the tall cedars of Lebanonand all the mighty oaks
        of Bashan.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will level all the high mountainsand all the lofty hills.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will break down every high towerand every fortified wall.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will destroy all the great trading ships[[COMMENT(0)]]and every
        magnificent vessel.  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:16 '
        content: Hebrew <b>every ship of Tarshish.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Human pride will be humbled,and human arrogance will be brought down.Only
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will be exaltedon that day of judgment.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Idols will completely disappear.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> rises to shake the earth,his
        enemies will crawl into holes in the ground.They will hide in caves in the
        rocksfrom the terror of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>and the glory of his
        majesty.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'On that day of judgment they will abandon the gold and silver idolsthey
        made for themselves to worship.They will leave their gods to the rodents
        and bats,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'while they crawl away into cavernsand hide among the jagged rocks
        in the cliffs.They will try to escape the terror of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>and
        the glory of his majestyas he rises to shake the earth.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Judgment against Judah
      content: "  The Lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,will
        take away from Jerusalem and Judaheverything they depend on:every bit of
        breadand every drop of water,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'all their heroes and soldiers,judges and prophets,fortune-tellers
        and elders,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'army officers and high officials,advisers, skilled sorcerers, and
        astrologers.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will make boys their leaders,and toddlers their rulers.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "People will oppress each other\u2014man against man,neighbor against
        neighbor.Young people will insult their elders,and vulgar people will sneer
        at the honorable.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In those days a man will say to his brother,\u201CSince you have
        a coat, you be our leader!Take charge of this heap of ruins!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But he will reply,\u201CNo! I can\u2019t help.I don\u2019t have any
        extra food or clothes.Don\u2019t put me in charge!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For Jerusalem will stumble,and Judah will fall,because they speak
        out against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and refuse to obey him.They provoke
        him to his face.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The very look on their faces gives them away.They display their sin
        like the people of Sodomand don\u2019t even try to hide it.They are doomed!They
        have brought destruction upon themselves.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Tell the godly that all will be well for them.They will enjoy the
        rich reward they have earned!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the wicked are doomed,for they will get exactly what they deserve.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Childish leaders oppress my people,and women rule over them.O my
        people, your leaders mislead you;they send you down the wrong road.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> takes his place in courtand presents
        his case against his people.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:13 '
        content: As in Greek and Syriac versions; Hebrew reads <b>against the peoples.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord </smallcaps>comes forward to pronounce judgmenton
        the elders and rulers of his people:\u201CYou have ruined Israel, my vineyard.Your
        houses are filled with things stolen from the poor.  "
      comments: []
    - title: A Warning to Jerusalem
      content: "How dare you crush my people,grinding the faces of the poor into
        the dust?\u201Ddemands the Lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says, \u201CBeautiful Zion[[COMMENT(0)]]
        is haughty:craning her elegant neck,flirting with her eyes,walking with dainty
        steps,tinkling her ankle bracelets.  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:16 '
        content: Or <b>The women of Zion </b>(with corresponding changes to plural
          forms through verse 24); Hebrew reads <b>The daughters of Zion; </b>also
          in 3:17.
    - title: 
      content: "So the Lord will send scabs on her head;the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will make beautiful Zion bald.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'On that day of judgmentthe Lord will strip away everything that makes
        her beautiful:ornaments, headbands, crescent necklaces,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'earrings, bracelets, and veils;  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'scarves, ankle bracelets, sashes,perfumes, and charms;  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'rings, jewels,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'party clothes, gowns, capes, and purses;  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'mirrors, fine linen garments,head ornaments, and shawls.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Instead of smelling of sweet perfume, she will stink.She will wear
        a rope for a sash,and her elegant hair will fall out.She will wear rough
        burlap instead of rich robes.Shame will replace her beauty.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:24 '
        content: As in Dead Sea Scrolls; Masoretic Text reads <b>robes / because
          instead of beauty.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'The men of the city will be killed with the sword,and her warriors
        will die in battle.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Promise of Restoration
      content: "  In that day so few men will be left that seven women will fight
        for each man, saying, \u201CLet us all marry you! We will provide our own
        food and clothing. Only let us take your name so we won\u2019t be mocked
        as old maids.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But in that day, the branch[[COMMENT(0)]] of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>will
        be beautiful and glorious;the fruit of the land will be the pride and gloryof
        all who survive in Israel.  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:2 '
        content: Or <b>the Branch.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "All who remain in Zionwill be a holy people\u2014those who survive
        the destruction of Jerusalemand are recorded among the living.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The Lord will wash the filth from beautiful Zion[[COMMENT(0)]]and
        cleanse Jerusalem of its bloodstainswith the hot breath of fiery judgment.  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:4 '
        content: Or <b>from the women of Zion; </b>Hebrew reads <b>from the daughters
          of Zion.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will provide shade for Mount
        Zionand all who assemble there.He will provide a canopy of cloud during the
        dayand smoke and flaming fire at night,covering the glorious land.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "A Song about the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Vineyard"
      content: '  Now I will sing for the one I lovea song about his vineyard:My
        beloved had a vineyardon a rich and fertile hill.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He plowed the land, cleared its stones,and planted it with the best
        vines.In the middle he built a watchtowerand carved a winepress in the nearby
        rocks.Then he waited for a harvest of sweet grapes,but the grapes that grew
        were bitter.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Now, you people of Jerusalem and Judah,you judge between me and my
        vineyard.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'What more could I have done for my vineyardthat I have not already
        done?When I expected sweet grapes,why did my vineyard give me bitter grapes?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Now let me tell youwhat I will do to my vineyard:I will tear down
        its hedgesand let it be destroyed.I will break down its wallsand let the
        animals trample it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will make it a wild placewhere the vines are not pruned and the
        ground is not hoed,a place overgrown with briers and thorns.I will command
        the cloudsto drop no rain on it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: "Judah\u2019s Guilt and Judgment"
      content: "The nation of Israel is the vineyard of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies.The people of Judah are his pleasant garden.He expected
        a crop of justice,but instead he found oppression.He expected to find righteousness,but
        instead he heard cries of violence.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'What sorrow for you who buy up house after house and field after
        field,until everyone is evicted and you live alone in the land.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But I have heard the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armiesswear a solemn oath:\u201CMany houses will stand deserted;even beautiful
        mansions will be empty.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Ten acres[[COMMENT(0)]] of vineyard will not produce even six gallons[[COMMENT(1)]]
        of wine.Ten baskets of seed will yield only one basket[[COMMENT(2)]] of grain.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:10a '
        content: Hebrew <b>A ten yoke, </b>that is, the area of land plowed by ten
          teams of oxen in one day.
      - number: '5:10b '
        content: Hebrew <b>a bath </b>[21 liters].
      - number: '5:10c '
        content: Hebrew <b>A homer </b>[5 bushels or 220 liters] <b>of seed will
          yield only an ephah </b>[20 quarts or 22 liters].
    - title: 
      content: 'What sorrow for those who get up early in the morninglooking for
        a drink of alcoholand spend long evenings drinking wineto make themselves
        flaming drunk.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They furnish wine and lovely music at their grand parties\u2014lyre
        and harp, tambourine and flute\u2014but they never think about the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>or
        notice what he is doing.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So my people will go into exile far awaybecause they do not know
        me.Those who are great and honored will starve,and the common people will
        die of thirst.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The grave[[COMMENT(0)]] is licking its lips in anticipation,opening
        its mouth wide.The great and the lowlyand all the drunken mob will be swallowed
        up.  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:14 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Sheol.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Humanity will be destroyed, and people brought down;even the arrogant
        will lower their eyes in humiliation.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies will
        be exalted by his justice.The holiness of God will be displayed by his righteousness.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In that day lambs will find good pastures,and fattened sheep and
        young goats[[COMMENT(0)]] will feed among the ruins.  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:17 '
        content: As in Greek version; Hebrew reads <b>and strangers.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'What sorrow for those who drag their sins behind themwith ropes made
        of lies,who drag wickedness behind them like a cart!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They even mock God and say,\u201CHurry up and do something!We want
        to see what you can do.Let the Holy One of Israel carry out his plan,for
        we want to know what it is.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'What sorrow for those who saythat evil is good and good is evil,that
        dark is light and light is dark,that bitter is sweet and sweet is bitter.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'What sorrow for those who are wise in their own eyesand think themselves
        so clever.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'What sorrow for those who are heroes at drinking wineand boast about
        all the alcohol they can hold.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They take bribes to let the wicked go free,and they punish the innocent.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, just as fire licks up stubbleand dry grass shrivels in
        the flame,so their roots will rotand their flowers wither.For they have rejected
        the law of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies;they have
        despised the word of the Holy One of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "That is why the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s anger burns against
        his people,and why he has raised his fist to crush them.The mountains tremble,and
        the corpses of his people litter the streets like garbage.But even then the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s anger is not satisfied.His fist is still
        poised to strike!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will send a signal to distant nations far awayand whistle to those
        at the ends of the earth.They will come racing toward Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will not get tired or stumble.They will not stop for rest or
        sleep.Not a belt will be loose,not a sandal strap broken.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their arrows will be sharpand their bows ready for battle.Sparks
        will fly from their horses\u2019 hooves,and the wheels of their chariots
        will spin like a whirlwind.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will roar like lions,like the strongest of lions.Growling, they
        will pounce on their victims and carry them off,and no one will be there
        to rescue them.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Isaiah\u2019s Cleansing and Call"
      content: '  It was in the year King Uzziah died[[COMMENT(0)]] that I saw the
        Lord. He was sitting on a lofty throne, and the train of his robe filled
        the Temple. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:1 '
        content: King Uzziah died in 740 <span class="ChapterContent_sc__Hg9da">b.c.</span>
    - title: 
      content: 'Attending him were mighty seraphim, each having six wings. With two
        wings they covered their faces, with two they covered their feet, and with
        two they flew. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They were calling out to each other,\u201CHoly, holy, holy is the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies!The whole earth is filled
        with his glory!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their voices shook the Temple to its foundations, and the entire
        building was filled with smoke.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then I said, \u201CIt\u2019s all over! I am doomed, for I am a sinful
        man. I have filthy lips, and I live among a people with filthy lips. Yet
        I have seen the King, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then one of the seraphim flew to me with a burning coal he had taken
        from the altar with a pair of tongs. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He touched my lips with it and said, \u201CSee, this coal has touched
        your lips. Now your guilt is removed, and your sins are forgiven.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then I heard the Lord asking, \u201CWhom should I send as a messenger
        to this people? Who will go for us?\u201DI said, \u201CHere I am. Send me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And he said, \u201CYes, go, and say to this people,\u2018Listen carefully,
        but do not understand.Watch closely, but learn nothing.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Harden the hearts of these people.Plug their ears and shut their
        eyes.That way, they will not see with their eyes,nor hear with their ears,nor
        understand with their heartsand turn to me for healing.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:9-10 '
        content: "Greek version reads <b>And he said, \u201CGo and say to this people,
          / \u2018When you hear what I say, you will not understand. / When you see
          what I do, you will not comprehend.\u2019 / For the hearts of these people
          are hardened, / and their ears cannot hear, and they have closed their
          eyes\u2014 / so their eyes cannot see, / and their ears cannot hear, /
          and their hearts cannot understand, / and they cannot turn to me and let
          me heal them.\u201D </b>Compare Matt 13:14-15; Mark 4:12; Luke 8:10; Acts
          28:26-27."
    - title: 
      content: "Then I said, \u201CLord, how long will this go on?\u201DAnd he replied,\u201CUntil
        their towns are empty,their houses are deserted,and the whole country is
        a wasteland;  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'until the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has sent everyone away,and
        the entire land of Israel lies deserted.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Message for Ahaz
      content: '  When Ahaz, son of Jotham and grandson of Uzziah, was king of Judah,
        King Rezin of Syria[[COMMENT(0)]] and Pekah son of Remaliah, the king of
        Israel, set out to attack Jerusalem. However, they were unable to carry out
        their plan.  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Aram; </b>also in 7:2, 4, 5, 8.
    - title: 
      content: "The news had come to the royal court of Judah: \u201CSyria is allied
        with Israel[[COMMENT(0)]] against us!\u201D So the hearts of the king and
        his people trembled with fear, like trees shaking in a storm.  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:2 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Ephraim, </b>referring to the northern kingdom of Israel;
          also in 7:5, 8, 9, 17.
    - title: 
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Isaiah, \u201CTake your
        son Shear-jashub[[COMMENT(0)]] and go out to meet King Ahaz. You will find
        him at the end of the aqueduct that feeds water into the upper pool, near
        the road leading to the field where cloth is washed.[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:3a '
        content: "<b>Shear-jashub </b>means \u201CA remnant will return.\u201D"
      - number: '7:3b '
        content: Or <b>bleached.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Tell him to stop worrying. Tell him he doesn\u2019t need to fear
        the fierce anger of those two burned-out embers, King Rezin of Syria and
        Pekah son of Remaliah. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, the kings of Syria and Israel are plotting against him, saying, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018We will attack Judah and capture it for ourselves. Then we
        will install the son of Tabeel as Judah\u2019s king.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But this is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CThis
        invasion will never happen;it will never take place;  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'for Syria is no stronger than its capital, Damascus,and Damascus
        is no stronger than its king, Rezin.As for Israel, within sixty-five yearsit
        will be crushed and completely destroyed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: The Sign of Immanuel
      content: "Israel is no stronger than its capital, Samaria,and Samaria is no
        stronger than its king, Pekah son of Remaliah.Unless your faith is firm,I
        cannot make you stand firm.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Later, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> sent this message to King
        Ahaz: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAsk the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God for a sign of
        confirmation, Ahaz. Make it as difficult as you want\u2014as high as heaven
        or as deep as the place of the dead.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:11 '
        content: Hebrew <b>as deep as Sheol.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "But the king refused. \u201CNo,\u201D he said, \u201CI will not test
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> like that.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Isaiah said, \u201CListen well, you royal family of David! Isn\u2019t
        it enough to exhaust human patience? Must you exhaust the patience of my
        God as well? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All right then, the Lord himself will give you the sign. Look! The
        virgin[[COMMENT(0)]] will conceive a child! She will give birth to a son
        and will call him Immanuel (which means \u2018God is with us\u2019). "
      comments:
      - number: '7:14 '
        content: Or <b>young woman.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'By the time this child is old enough to choose what is right and
        reject what is wrong, he will be eating yogurt[[COMMENT(0)]] and honey. '
      comments:
      - number: '7:15 '
        content: Or <b>curds; </b>also in 7:22.
    - title: 
      content: 'For before the child is that old, the lands of the two kings you
        fear so much will both be deserted.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will bring things on you,
        your nation, and your family unlike anything since Israel broke away from
        Judah. He will bring the king of Assyria upon you!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In that day the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will whistle for the
        army of southern Egypt and for the army of Assyria. They will swarm around
        you like flies and bees. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will come in vast hordes and settle in the fertile areas and
        also in the desolate valleys, caves, and thorny places. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In that day the Lord will hire a \u201Crazor\u201D from beyond the
        Euphrates River[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014the king of Assyria\u2014and use it to
        shave off everything: your land, your crops, and your people.[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:20a '
        content: Hebrew <b>the river.</b>
      - number: '7:20b '
        content: Hebrew <b>shave off the head, the hair of the legs, and the beard.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'In that day a farmer will be fortunate to have a cow and two sheep
        or goats left. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Nevertheless, there will be enough milk for everyone because so few
        people will be left in the land. They will eat their fill of yogurt and honey. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In that day the lush vineyards, now worth 1,000 pieces of silver,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        will become patches of briers and thorns. '
      comments:
      - number: '7:23 '
        content: Hebrew <b>1,000 [shekels] of silver, </b>about 25 pounds or 11.4
          kilograms in weight.
    - title: 
      content: 'The entire land will become a vast expanse of briers and thorns,
        a hunting ground overrun by wildlife. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Coming Assyrian Invasion
      content: "  Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to me, \u201CMake a large
        signboard and clearly write this name on it: Maher-shalal-hash-baz.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '8:1 '
        content: "<b>Maher-shalal-hash-baz </b>means \u201CSwift to plunder and quick
          to carry away.\u201D"
    - title: 
      content: 'I asked Uriah the priest and Zechariah son of Jeberekiah, both known
        as honest men, to witness my doing this.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then I slept with my wife, and she became pregnant and gave birth
        to a son. And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CCall him Maher-shalal-hash-baz. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For before this child is old enough to say \u2018Papa\u2019 or \u2018Mama,\u2019
        the king of Assyria will carry away both the abundance of Damascus and the
        riches of Samaria.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke to me again and said, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CMy care for the people of Judah is like the gently flowing
        waters of Shiloah, but they have rejected it. They are rejoicing over what
        will happen to[[COMMENT(0)]] King Rezin and King Pekah.[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:6a '
        content: Or <b>They are rejoicing because of.</b>
      - number: '8:6b '
        content: Hebrew <b>and the son of Remaliah.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, the Lord will overwhelm them with a mighty flood from
        the Euphrates River[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014the king of Assyria and all his glory.
        This flood will overflow all its channels "
      comments:
      - number: '8:7 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the river.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'and sweep into Judah until it is chin deep. It will spread its wings,
        submerging your land from one end to the other, O Immanuel.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHuddle together, you nations, and be terrified.Listen, all
        you distant lands.Prepare for battle, but you will be crushed!Yes, prepare
        for battle, but you will be crushed!  "
      comments: []
    - title: A Call to Trust the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
      content: "Call your councils of war, but they will be worthless.Develop your
        strategies, but they will not succeed.For God is with us![[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:10 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Immanuel!</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has given me a strong warning not
        to think like everyone else does. He said,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CDon\u2019t call everything a conspiracy, like they do,and don\u2019t
        live in dread of what frightens them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Make the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies holy
        in your life.He is the one you should fear.He is the one who should make
        you tremble.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will keep you safe.But to Israel and Judahhe will be a stone that
        makes people stumble,a rock that makes them fall.And for the people of Jerusalemhe
        will be a trap and a snare.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Many will stumble and fall,never to rise again.They will be snared
        and captured.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Preserve the teaching of God;entrust his instructions to those who
        follow me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will wait for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,who has turned away
        from the descendants of Jacob.I will put my hope in him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I and the children the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has given me serve
        as signs and warnings to Israel from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies who dwells in his Temple on Mount Zion.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Someone may say to you, \u201CLet\u2019s ask the mediums and those
        who consult the spirits of the dead. With their whisperings and mutterings,
        they will tell us what to do.\u201D But shouldn\u2019t people ask God for
        guidance? Should the living seek guidance from the dead?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Look to God\u2019s instructions and teachings! People who contradict
        his word are completely in the dark. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will go from one place to another, weary and hungry. And because
        they are hungry, they will rage and curse their king and their God. They
        will look up to heaven '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Hope in the Messiah
      content: '    [[COMMENT(0)]]Nevertheless, that time of darkness and despair
        will not go on forever. The land of Zebulun and Naphtali will be humbled,
        but there will be a time in the future when Galilee of the Gentiles, which
        lies along the road that runs between the Jordan and the sea, will be filled
        with glory.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:1 '
        content: '  Verse 9:1 is numbered 8:23 in Hebrew text.    '
    - title: 
      content: '  [[COMMENT(0)]]The people who walk in darknesswill see a great light.For
        those who live in a land of deep darkness,[[COMMENT(1)]]a light will shine.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:2a '
        content: '  Verses 9:2-21 are numbered 9:1-20 in Hebrew text.  '
      - number: '9:2b '
        content: Greek version reads <b>a land where death casts its shadow. </b>Compare
          Matt 4:16.
    - title: 
      content: 'You will enlarge the nation of Israel,and its people will rejoice.They
        will rejoice before youas people rejoice at the harvestand like warriors
        dividing the plunder.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For you will break the yoke of their slaveryand lift the heavy burden
        from their shoulders.You will break the oppressor\u2019s rod,just as you
        did when you destroyed the army of Midian.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The boots of the warriorand the uniforms bloodstained by warwill
        all be burned.They will be fuel for the fire.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For a child is born to us,a son is given to us.The government will
        rest on his shoulders.And he will be called:Wonderful Counselor,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Mighty God,Everlasting Father, Prince of Peace.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:6 '
        content: Or <b>Wonderful, Counselor.</b>
    - title: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Anger against Israel"
      content: "His government and its peacewill never end.He will rule with fairness
        and justice from the throne of his ancestor Davidfor all eternity.The passionate
        commitment of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armieswill
        make this happen!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The Lord has spoken out against Jacob;his judgment has fallen upon
        Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And the people of Israel[[COMMENT(0)]] and Samaria,who spoke with
        such pride and arrogance,will soon know it.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:9 '
        content: Hebrew <b>of Ephraim, </b>referring to the northern kingdom of Israel.
    - title: 
      content: "They said, \u201CWe will replace the broken bricks of our ruins with
        finished stone,and replant the felled sycamore-fig trees with cedars.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will bring Rezin\u2019s enemies
        against Israeland stir up all their foes.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The Syrians[[COMMENT(0)]] from the east and the Philistines from
        the westwill bare their fangs and devour Israel.But even then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        anger will not be satisfied.His fist is still poised to strike.  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:12 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Arameans.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "For after all this punishment, the people will still not repent.They
        will not seek the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Therefore, in a single day the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will destroy
        both the head and the tail,the noble palm branch and the lowly reed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The leaders of Israel are the head,and the lying prophets are the
        tail.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the leaders of the people have misled them.They have led them
        down the path of destruction.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "That is why the Lord takes no pleasure in the young menand shows
        no mercy even to the widows and orphans.For they are all wicked hypocrites,and
        they all speak foolishness.But even then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        anger will not be satisfied.His fist is still poised to strike.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This wickedness is like a brushfire.It burns not only briers and
        thornsbut also sets the forests ablaze.Its burning sends up clouds of smoke.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The land will be blackenedby the fury of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies.The people will be fuel for the fire,and no one will
        spare even his own brother.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will attack their neighbor on the rightbut will still be hungry.They
        will devour their neighbor on the leftbut will not be satisfied.In the end
        they will even eat their own children.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:20 '
        content: Or <b>eat their own arms.</b>
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  What sorrow awaits the unjust judgesand those who issue unfair
        laws.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They deprive the poor of justiceand deny the rights of the needy
        among my people.They prey on widowsand take advantage of orphans.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'What will you do when I punish you,when I send disaster upon you
        from a distant land?To whom will you turn for help?Where will your treasures
        be safe?  '
      comments: []
    - title: Judgment against Assyria
      content: "You will stumble along as prisonersor lie among the dead.But even
        then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s anger will not be satisfied.His
        fist is still poised to strike.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhat sorrow awaits Assyria, the rod of my anger.I use it as
        a club to express my anger.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am sending Assyria against a godless nation,against a people with
        whom I am angry.Assyria will plunder them,trampling them like dirt beneath
        its feet.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the king of Assyria will not understand that he is my tool;his
        mind does not work that way.His plan is simply to destroy,to cut down nation
        after nation.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He will say,\u2018Each of my princes will soon be a king.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We destroyed Calno just as we did Carchemish.Hamath fell before us
        as Arpad did.And we destroyed Samaria just as we did Damascus.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, we have finished off many a kingdomwhose gods were greater than
        those in Jerusalem and Samaria.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So we will defeat Jerusalem and her gods,just as we destroyed Samaria
        with hers.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "After the Lord has used the king of Assyria to accomplish his purposes
        on Mount Zion and in Jerusalem, he will turn against the king of Assyria
        and punish him\u2014for he is proud and arrogant. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He boasts,\u201CBy my own powerful arm I have done this.With my own
        shrewd wisdom I planned it.I have broken down the defenses of nationsand
        carried off their treasures.I have knocked down their kings like a bull.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I have robbed their nests of richesand gathered up kingdoms as a
        farmer gathers eggs.No one can even flap a wing against meor utter a peep
        of protest.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But can the ax boast greater power than the person who uses it?Is
        the saw greater than the person who saws?Can a rod strike unless a hand moves
        it?Can a wooden cane walk by itself?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, the Lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies,will send a plague among Assyria\u2019s proud troops,and a flaming
        fire will consume its glory.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the Light of Israel, will be a fire;the
        Holy One will be a flame.He will devour the thorns and briers with fire,burning
        up the enemy in a single night.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will consume Assyria\u2019s glorylike
        a fire consumes a forest in a fruitful land;it will waste away like sick
        people in a plague.  "
      comments: []
    - title: "Hope for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s People"
      content: "Of all that glorious forest, only a few trees will survive\u2014so
        few that a child could count them!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In that day the remnant left in Israel,the survivors in the house
        of Jacob,will no longer depend on allieswho seek to destroy them.But they
        will faithfully trust the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,the Holy One of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A remnant will return;[[COMMENT(0)]]yes, the remnant of Jacob will
        return to the Mighty God.  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:21 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Shear-jashub; </b>see 7:3; 8:18.
    - title: 
      content: 'But though the people of Israel are as numerousas the sand of the
        seashore,only a remnant of them will return.The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has rightly decided to destroy his people.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yes, the Lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,has
        already decided to destroy the entire land.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:22-23 '
        content: Greek version reads <b>only a remnant of them will be saved. / For
          he will carry out his sentence quickly and with finality and righteousness;
          / for God will carry out his sentence upon all the world with finality.
          </b>Compare Rom 9:27-28.
    - title: 
      content: "So this is what the Lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, says: \u201CO my people in Zion, do not be afraid of the Assyrians
        when they oppress you with rod and club as the Egyptians did long ago. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In a little while my anger against you will end, and then my anger
        will rise up to destroy them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies will lash
        them with his whip, as he did when Gideon triumphed over the Midianites at
        the rock of Oreb, or when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s staff was
        raised to drown the Egyptian army in the sea.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In that day the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will end the bondage
        of his people.He will break the yoke of slaveryand lift it from their shoulders.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:27 '
        content: As in Greek version; Hebrew reads <b>The yoke will be broken, /
          for you have grown so fat.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Look, the Assyrians are now at Aiath.They are passing through Migronand
        are storing their equipment at Micmash.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They are crossing the passand are camping at Geba.Fear strikes the
        town of Ramah.All the people of Gibeah, the hometown of Saul,are running
        for their lives.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Scream in terror,you people of Gallim!Shout out a warning to Laishah.Oh,
        poor Anathoth!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'There go the people of Madmenah, all fleeing.The citizens of Gebim
        are trying to hide.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The enemy stops at Nob for the rest of that day.He shakes his fist
        at beautiful Mount Zion, the mountain of Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But look! The Lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies,will chop down the mighty tree of Assyria with great power!He will
        cut down the proud.That lofty tree will be brought down.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "A Branch from David\u2019s Line"
      content: "  Out of the stump of David\u2019s family[[COMMENT(0)]] will grow
        a shoot\u2014yes, a new Branch bearing fruit from the old root.  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:1 '
        content: "Hebrew <b>the stump of the line of Jesse. </b>Jesse was King David\u2019s
          father."
    - title: 
      content: "And the Spirit of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will rest on him\u2014the
        Spirit of wisdom and understanding,the Spirit of counsel and might,the Spirit
        of knowledge and the fear of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will delight in obeying the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.He will
        not judge by appearancenor make a decision based on hearsay.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will give justice to the poorand make fair decisions for the exploited.The
        earth will shake at the force of his word,and one breath from his mouth will
        destroy the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will wear righteousness like a beltand truth like an undergarment.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In that day the wolf and the lamb will live together;the leopard
        will lie down with the baby goat.The calf and the yearling will be safe with
        the lion,and a little child will lead them all.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The cow will graze near the bear.The cub and the calf will lie down
        together.The lion will eat hay like a cow.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The baby will play safely near the hole of a cobra.Yes, a little
        child will put its hand in a nest of deadly snakes without harm.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Nothing will hurt or destroy in all my holy mountain,for as the waters
        fill the sea,so the earth will be filled with people who know the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In that day the heir to David\u2019s throne[[COMMENT(0)]]will be
        a banner of salvation to all the world.The nations will rally to him,and
        the land where he lives will be a glorious place.[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:10a '
        content: Hebrew <b>the root of Jesse.</b>
      - number: '11:10b '
        content: "Greek version reads <b>In that day the heir to David\u2019s throne
          </b>[literally <b>the root of Jesse</b>] <b>will come, / and he will rule
          over the Gentiles. / They will place their hopes on him. </b>Compare Rom
          15:12."
    - title: 
      content: "In that day the Lord will reach out his hand a second timeto bring
        back the remnant of his people\u2014those who remain in Assyria and northern
        Egypt;in southern Egypt, Ethiopia,[[COMMENT(0)]] and Elam;in Babylonia,[[COMMENT(1)]]
        Hamath, and all the distant coastlands.  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:11a '
        content: Hebrew <b>in Pathros, Cush.</b>
      - number: '11:11b '
        content: Hebrew <b>in Shinar.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'He will raise a flag among the nationsand assemble the exiles of
        Israel.He will gather the scattered people of Judahfrom the ends of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then at last the jealousy between Israel[[COMMENT(0)]] and Judah
        will end.They will not be rivals anymore.  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:13 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Ephraim, </b>referring to the northern kingdom of Israel.
    - title: 
      content: 'They will join forces to swoop down on Philistia to the west.Together
        they will attack and plunder the nations to the east.They will occupy the
        lands of Edom and Moab,and Ammon will obey them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will make a dry path through the
        gulf of the Red Sea.[[COMMENT(0)]]He will wave his hand over the Euphrates
        River,[[COMMENT(1)]]sending a mighty wind to divide it into seven streamsso
        it can easily be crossed on foot.  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:15a '
        content: Hebrew <b>will destroy the tongue of the sea of Egypt.</b>
      - number: '11:15b '
        content: Hebrew <b>the river.</b>
  - verses:
    - title: Songs of Praise for Salvation
      content: "  In that day you will sing:\u201CI will praise you, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!You
        were angry with me, but not anymore.Now you comfort me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "See, God has come to save me.I will trust in him and not be afraid.The
        <smallcaps>Lord God</smallcaps> is my strength and my song;he has given me
        victory.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'With joy you will drink deeplyfrom the fountain of salvation!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In that wonderful day you will sing:\u201CThank the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!
        Praise his name!Tell the nations what he has done.Let them know how mighty
        he is!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Sing to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, for he has done wonderful
        things.Make known his praise around the world.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Message about Babylon
      content: '  Isaiah son of Amoz received this message concerning the destruction
        of Babylon:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CRaise a signal flag on a bare hilltop.Call up an army against
        Babylon.Wave your hand to encourage themas they march into the palaces of
        the high and mighty.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have dedicated these soldiers
        for this task.Yes, I have called mighty warriors to express my anger,and
        they will rejoice when I am exalted.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Hear the noise on the mountains!Listen, as the vast armies march!It
        is the noise and shouting of many nations.The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies has called this army together.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They come from distant countries,from beyond the farthest horizons.They
        are the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s weapons to carry out his anger.With
        them he will destroy the whole land.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Scream in terror, for the day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has arrived\u2014the time for the Almighty to destroy.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Every arm is paralyzed with fear.Every heart melts,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and people are terrified.Pangs of anguish grip them,like those of
        a woman in labor.They look helplessly at one another,their faces aflame with
        fear.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For see, the day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is coming\u2014the
        terrible day of his fury and fierce anger.The land will be made desolate,and
        all the sinners destroyed with it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The heavens will be black above them;the stars will give no light.The
        sun will be dark when it rises,and the moon will provide no light.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, will punish the world for
        its eviland the wicked for their sin.I will crush the arrogance of the proudand
        humble the pride of the mighty.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will make people scarcer than gold\u2014more rare than the fine
        gold of Ophir.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I will shake the heavens.The earth will move from its placewhen
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies displays his wrathin
        the day of his fierce anger.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Everyone in Babylon will run about like a hunted gazelle,like sheep
        without a shepherd.They will try to find their own peopleand flee to their
        own land.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Anyone who is captured will be cut down\u2014run through with a sword.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their little children will be dashed to death before their eyes.Their
        homes will be sacked, and their wives will be raped.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CLook, I will stir up the Medes against Babylon.They cannot
        be tempted by silveror bribed with gold.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The attacking armies will shoot down the young men with arrows.They
        will have no mercy on helpless babiesand will show no compassion for children.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Babylon, the most glorious of kingdoms,the flower of Chaldean pride,will
        be devastated like Sodom and Gomorrahwhen God destroyed them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Babylon will never be inhabited again.It will remain empty for generation
        after generation.Nomads will refuse to camp there,and shepherds will not
        bed down their sheep.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Desert animals will move into the ruined city,and the houses will
        be haunted by howling creatures.Owls will live among the ruins,and wild goats
        will go there to dance.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "A Taunt for Babylon\u2019s King"
      content: '  But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will have mercy on the descendants
        of Jacob. He will choose Israel as his special people once again. He will
        bring them back to settle once again in their own land. And people from many
        different nations will come and join them there and unite with the people
        of Israel.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:1 '
        content: "Hebrew <b>the house of Jacob. </b>The names \u201CJacob\u201D and
          \u201CIsrael\u201D are often interchanged throughout the Old Testament,
          referring sometimes to the individual patriarch and sometimes to the nation."
    - title: 
      content: "The nations of the world will help the people of Israel to return,
        and those who come to live in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s land
        will serve them. Those who captured Israel will themselves be captured, and
        Israel will rule over its enemies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In that wonderful day when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gives
        his people rest from sorrow and fear, from slavery and chains, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "you will taunt the king of Babylon. You will say,\u201CThe mighty
        man has been destroyed.Yes, your insolence[[COMMENT(0)]] is ended.  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:4 '
        content: As in Dead Sea Scrolls; the meaning of the Masoretic Text is uncertain.
    - title: 
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has crushed your wicked powerand
        broken your evil rule.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You struck the people with endless blows of rageand held the nations
        in your angry gripwith unrelenting tyranny.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But finally the earth is at rest and quiet.Now it can sing again!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Even the trees of the forest\u2014the cypress trees and the cedars
        of Lebanon\u2014sing out this joyous song:\u2018Since you have been cut down,no
        one will come now to cut us down!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIn the place of the dead[[COMMENT(0)]] there is excitementover
        your arrival.The spirits of world leaders and mighty kings long deadstand
        up to see you.  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:9 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Sheol; </b>also in 14:15.
    - title: 
      content: "With one voice they all cry out,\u2018Now you are as weak as we are!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your might and power were buried with you.[[COMMENT(0)]]The sound
        of the harp in your palace has ceased.Now maggots are your sheet,and worms
        your blanket.\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:11 '
        content: Hebrew <b>were brought down to Sheol.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHow you are fallen from heaven,O shining star, son of the morning!You
        have been thrown down to the earth,you who destroyed the nations of the world.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For you said to yourself,\u2018I will ascend to heaven and set my
        throne above God\u2019s stars.I will preside on the mountain of the godsfar
        away in the north.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:13 '
        content: Or <b>on the heights of Zaphon.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "I will climb to the highest heavensand be like the Most High.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Instead, you will be brought down to the place of the dead,down to
        its lowest depths.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Everyone there will stare at you and ask,\u2018Can this be the one
        who shook the earthand made the kingdoms of the world tremble?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Is this the one who destroyed the worldand made it into a wasteland?Is
        this the king who demolished the world\u2019s greatest citiesand had no mercy
        on his prisoners?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe kings of the nations lie in stately glory,each in his own
        tomb,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'but you will be thrown out of your gravelike a worthless branch.Like
        a corpse trampled underfoot,you will be dumped into a mass gravewith those
        killed in battle.You will descend to the pit.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will not be given a proper burial,for you have destroyed your
        nationand slaughtered your people.The descendants of such an evil personwill
        never again receive honor.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Kill this man\u2019s children!Let them die because of their father\u2019s
        sins!They must not rise and conquer the earth,filling the world with their
        cities.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies
        says:\u201CI, myself, have risen against Babylon!I will destroy its children
        and its children\u2019s children,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - title: A Message about Assyria
      content: "\u201CI will make Babylon a desolate place of owls,filled with swamps
        and marshes.I will sweep the land with the broom of destruction.I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies, have spoken!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies has sworn
        this oath:\u201CIt will all happen as I have planned.It will be as I have
        decided.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will break the Assyrians when they are in Israel;I will trample
        them on my mountains.My people will no longer be their slavesnor bow down
        under their heavy loads.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I have a plan for the whole earth,a hand of judgment upon all the
        nations.  '
      comments: []
    - title: A Message about Philistia
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies has spoken\u2014who
        can change his plans?When his hand is raised,who can stop him?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This message came to me the year King Ahaz died:[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:28 '
        content: King Ahaz died in 715 <span class="ChapterContent_sc__Hg9da">b.c.</span>
    - title: 
      content: "Do not rejoice, you Philistines,that the rod that struck you is broken\u2014that
        the king who attacked you is dead.For from that snake a more poisonous snake
        will be born,a fiery serpent to destroy you!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will feed the poor in my pasture;the needy will lie down in peace.But
        as for you, I will wipe you out with famineand destroy the few who remain.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Wail at the gates! Weep in the cities!Melt with fear, you Philistines!A
        powerful army comes like smoke from the north.Each soldier rushes forward
        eager to fight.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Message about Moab
      content: '  This message came to me concerning Moab:In one night the town of
        Ar will be leveled,and the city of Kir will be destroyed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your people will go to their temple in Dibon to mourn.They will go
        to their sacred shrines to weep.They will wail for the fate of Nebo and Medeba,shaving
        their heads in sorrow and cutting off their beards.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will wear burlap as they wander the streets.From every home
        and public square will come the sound of wailing.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The people of Heshbon and Elealeh will cry out;their voices will
        be heard as far away as Jahaz!The bravest warriors of Moab will cry out in
        utter terror.They will be helpless with fear.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My heart weeps for Moab.Its people flee to Zoar and Eglath-shelishiyah.Weeping,
        they climb the road to Luhith.Their cries of distress can be heard all along
        the road to Horonaim.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Even the waters of Nimrim are dried up!The grassy banks are scorched.The
        tender plants are gone;nothing green remains.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The people grab their possessionsand carry them across the Ravine
        of Willows.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A cry of distress echoes through the land of Moabfrom one end to
        the other\u2014from Eglaim to Beer-elim.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  Send lambs from Sela as tributeto the ruler of the land.Send them
        through the desertto the mountain of beautiful Zion.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The women of Moab are left like homeless birdsat the shallow crossings
        of the Arnon River.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHelp us,\u201D they cry.\u201CDefend us against our enemies.Protect
        us from their relentless attack.Do not betray us now that we have escaped.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Let our refugees stay among you.Hide them from our enemies until
        the terror is past.\u201DWhen oppression and destruction have endedand enemy
        raiders have disappeared,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "then God will establish one of David\u2019s descendants as king.He
        will rule with mercy and truth.He will always do what is justand be eager
        to do what is right.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "We have heard about proud Moab\u2014about its pride and arrogance
        and rage.But all that boasting has disappeared.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The entire land of Moab weeps.Yes, everyone in Moab mournsfor the
        cakes of raisins from Kir-hareseth.They are all gone now.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The farms of Heshbon are abandoned;the vineyards at Sibmah are deserted.The
        rulers of the nations have broken down Moab\u2014that beautiful grapevine.Its
        tendrils spread north as far as the town of Jazerand trailed eastward into
        the wilderness.Its shoots reached so far westthat they crossed over the Dead
        Sea.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '16:8 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the sea.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'So now I weep for Jazer and the vineyards of Sibmah;my tears will
        flow for Heshbon and Elealeh.There are no more shouts of joyover your summer
        fruits and harvest.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Gone now is the gladness,gone the joy of harvest.There will be no
        singing in the vineyards,no more happy shouts,no treading of grapes in the
        winepresses.I have ended all their harvest joys.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My heart\u2019s cry for Moab is like a lament on a harp.I am filled
        with anguish for Kir-hareseth.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '16:11 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Kir-heres, </b>a variant spelling of Kir-hareseth.
    - title: 
      content: 'The people of Moab will worship at their pagan shrines,but it will
        do them no good.They will cry to the gods in their temples,but no one will
        be able to save them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has already said these things about
        Moab in the past. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Message about Damascus and Israel
      content: "  This message came to me concerning Damascus:\u201CLook, the city
        of Damascus will disappear!It will become a heap of ruins.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The towns of Aroer will be deserted.Flocks will graze in the streets
        and lie down undisturbed,with no one to chase them away.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The fortified towns of Israel[[COMMENT(0)]] will also be destroyed,and
        the royal power of Damascus will end.All that remains of Syria[[COMMENT(1)]]will
        share the fate of Israel\u2019s departed glory,\u201Ddeclares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies.  "
      comments:
      - number: '17:3a '
        content: Hebrew <b>of Ephraim, </b>referring to the northern kingdom of Israel.
      - number: '17:3b '
        content: Hebrew <b>Aram.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIn that day Israel\u2019s[[COMMENT(0)]] glory will grow dim;its
        robust body will waste away.  "
      comments:
      - number: '17:4 '
        content: "Hebrew <b>Jacob\u2019s. </b>See note on 14:1."
    - title: 
      content: 'The whole land will look like a grainfieldafter the harvesters have
        gathered the grain.It will be desolate,like the fields in the valley of Rephaim
        after the harvest.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Only a few of its people will be left,like stray olives left on a
        tree after the harvest.Only two or three remain in the highest branches,four
        or five scattered here and there on the limbs,\u201Ddeclares the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then at last the people will look to their Creatorand turn their
        eyes to the Holy One of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will no longer look to their idols for helpor worship what their
        own hands have made.They will never again bow down to their Asherah polesor
        worship at the pagan shrines they have built.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their largest cities will be like a deserted forest,like the land
        the Hivites and Amorites abandoned[[COMMENT(0)]]when the Israelites came
        here so long ago.It will be utterly desolate.  '
      comments:
      - number: '17:9 '
        content: As in Greek version; Hebrew reads <b>like places of the wood and
          the highest bough.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Why? Because you have turned from the God who can save you.You have
        forgotten the Rock who can hide you.So you may plant the finest grapevinesand
        import the most expensive seedlings.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They may sprout on the day you set them out;yes, they may blossom
        on the very morning you plant them,but you will never pick any grapes from
        them.Your only harvest will be a load of grief and unrelieved pain.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Listen! The armies of many nationsroar like the roaring of the sea.Hear
        the thunder of the mighty forcesas they rush forward like thundering waves.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But though they thunder like breakers on a beach,God will silence
        them, and they will run away.They will flee like chaff scattered by the wind,like
        a tumbleweed whirling before a storm.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Message about Ethiopia
      content: "  Listen, Ethiopia[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014land of fluttering sails[[COMMENT(1)]]that
        lies at the headwaters of the Nile,  "
      comments:
      - number: '18:1a '
        content: Hebrew <b>Cush.</b>
      - number: '18:1b '
        content: Or <b>land of many locusts; </b>Hebrew reads <b>land of whirring
          wings.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'that sends ambassadorsin swift boats down the river.Go, swift messengers!Take
        a message to a tall, smooth-skinned people,who are feared far and widefor
        their conquests and destruction,and whose land is divided by rivers.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All you people of the world,everyone who lives on the earth\u2014when
        I raise my battle flag on the mountain, look!When I blow the ram\u2019s horn,
        listen!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has told me this:\u201CI will
        watch quietly from my dwelling place\u2014as quietly as the heat rises on
        a summer day,or as the morning dew forms during the harvest.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Even before you begin your attack,while your plans are ripening like
        grapes,the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will cut off your new growth with
        pruning shears.He will snip off and discard your spreading branches.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your mighty army will be left dead in the fieldsfor the mountain
        vultures and wild animals.The vultures will tear at the corpses all summer.The
        wild animals will gnaw at the bones all winter.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Message about Egypt
      content: '  This message came to me concerning Egypt:Look! The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is advancing against Egypt,riding on a swift cloud.The idols of Egypt tremble.The
        hearts of the Egyptians melt with fear.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI will make Egyptian fight against Egyptian\u2014brother against
        brother,neighbor against neighbor,city against city,province against province.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The Egyptians will lose heart,and I will confuse their plans.They
        will plead with their idols for wisdomand call on spirits, mediums, and those
        who consult the spirits of the dead.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will hand Egypt overto a hard, cruel master.A fierce king will
        rule them,\u201Dsays the Lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The waters of the Nile will fail to rise and flood the fields.The
        riverbed will be parched and dry.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The canals of the Nile will dry up,and the streams of Egypt will
        stinkwith rotting reeds and rushes.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'All the greenery along the riverbankand all the crops along the riverwill
        dry up and blow away.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The fishermen will lament for lack of work.Those who cast hooks into
        the Nile will groan,and those who use nets will lose heart.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'There will be no flax for the harvesters,no thread for the weavers.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will be in despair,and all the workers will be sick at heart.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'What fools are the officials of Zoan!Their best counsel to the king
        of Egypt is stupid and wrong.Will they still boast to Pharaoh of their wisdom?Will
        they dare brag about all their wise ancestors?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Where are your wise counselors, Pharaoh?Let them tell you what God
        plans,what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies is going
        to do to Egypt.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The officials of Zoan are fools,and the officials of Memphis[[COMMENT(0)]]
        are deluded.The leaders of the peoplehave led Egypt astray.  '
      comments:
      - number: '19:13 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Noph.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has sent a spirit of foolishness
        on them,so all their suggestions are wrong.They cause Egypt to staggerlike
        a drunk in his vomit.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "There is nothing Egypt can do.All are helpless\u2014the head and
        the tail,the noble palm branch and the lowly reed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In that day the Egyptians will be as weak as women. They will cower
        in fear beneath the upraised fist of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Just to speak the name of Israel will terrorize them, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies has laid out his plans against them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In that day five of Egypt\u2019s cities will follow the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies. They will even begin to speak Hebrew, the language
        of Canaan. One of these cities will be Heliopolis, the City of the Sun.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:18 '
        content: Or <b>will be the City of Destruction.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'In that day there will be an altar to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        in the heart of Egypt, and there will be a monument to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        at its border. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It will be a sign and a witness that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies is worshiped in the land of Egypt. When the people
        cry to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> for help against those who oppress
        them, he will send them a savior who will rescue them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will make himself known to the Egyptians.
        Yes, they will know the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and will give their sacrifices
        and offerings to him. They will make a vow to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and will keep it. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will strike Egypt, and then he will
        bring healing. For the Egyptians will turn to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and he will listen to their pleas and heal them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In that day Egypt and Assyria will be connected by a highway. The
        Egyptians and Assyrians will move freely between their lands, and they will
        both worship God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In that day Israel will be the third, along with Egypt and Assyria,
        a blessing in the midst of the earth. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Message about Egypt and Ethiopia
      content: '  In the year when King Sargon of Assyria sent his commander in chief
        to capture the Philistine city of Ashdod,[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '20:1 '
        content: Ashdod was captured by Assyria in 711 <span class="ChapterContent_sc__Hg9da">b.c.</span>
    - title: 
      content: "the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> told Isaiah son of Amoz, \u201CTake
        off the burlap you have been wearing, and remove your sandals.\u201D Isaiah
        did as he was told and walked around naked and barefoot.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CMy servant Isaiah
        has been walking around naked and barefoot for the last three years. This
        is a sign\u2014a symbol of the terrible troubles I will bring upon Egypt
        and Ethiopia.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '20:3 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Cush; </b>also in 20:5.
    - title: 
      content: 'For the king of Assyria will take away the Egyptians and Ethiopians[[COMMENT(0)]]
        as prisoners. He will make them walk naked and barefoot, both young and old,
        their buttocks bared, to the shame of Egypt. '
      comments:
      - number: '20:4 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Cushites.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the Philistines will be thrown into panic, for they counted
        on the power of Ethiopia and boasted of their allies in Egypt! '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Message about Babylon
      content: "  This message came to me concerning Babylon\u2014the desert by the
        sea[[COMMENT(0)]]:Disaster is roaring down on you from the desert,like a
        whirlwind sweeping in from the Negev.  "
      comments:
      - number: '21:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>concerning the desert by the sea.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'I see a terrifying vision:I see the betrayer betraying,the destroyer
        destroying.Go ahead, you Elamites and Medes,attack and lay siege.I will make
        an endto all the groaning Babylon caused.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My stomach aches and burns with pain.Sharp pangs of anguish are upon
        me,like those of a woman in labor.I grow faint when I hear what God is planning;I
        am too afraid to look.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My mind reels and my heart races.I longed for evening to come,but
        now I am terrified of the dark.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Look! They are preparing a great feast.They are spreading rugs for
        people to sit on.Everyone is eating and drinking.But quick! Grab your shields
        and prepare for battle.You are being attacked!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Meanwhile, the Lord said to me,\u201CPut a watchman on the city wall.Let
        him shout out what he sees.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He should look for chariotsdrawn by pairs of horses,and for riders
        on donkeys and camels.Let the watchman be fully alert.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the watchman[[COMMENT(0)]] called out,\u201CDay after day I
        have stood on the watchtower, my lord.Night after night I have remained at
        my post.  "
      comments:
      - number: '21:8 '
        content: As in Dead Sea Scrolls and Syriac version; Masoretic Text reads
          <b>a lion.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Now at last\u2014look!Here comes a man in a chariotwith a pair of
        horses!\u201DThen the watchman said,\u201CBabylon is fallen, fallen!All the
        idols of Babylonlie broken on the ground!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: A Message about Edom
      content: "O my people, threshed and winnowed,I have told you everything the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies has said,everything the
        God of Israel has told me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This message came to me concerning Edom[[COMMENT(0)]]:Someone from
        Edom[[COMMENT(1)]] keeps calling to me,\u201CWatchman, how much longer until
        morning?When will the night be over?\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '21:11a '
        content: "Hebrew <b>Dumah, </b>which means \u201Csilence\u201D or \u201Cstillness.\u201D
          It is a wordplay on the word <b>Edom.</b>"
      - number: '21:11b '
        content: Hebrew <b>Seir, </b>another name for Edom.
    - title: A Message about Arabia
      content: "The watchman replies,\u201CMorning is coming, but night will soon
        return.If you wish to ask again, then come back and ask.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This message came to me concerning Arabia:O caravans from Dedan,hide
        in the deserts of Arabia.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O people of Tema,bring water to these thirsty people,food to these
        weary refugees.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They have fled from the sword,from the drawn sword,from the bent
        bowand the terrors of battle.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The Lord said to me, \u201CWithin a year, counting each day,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        all the glory of Kedar will come to an end. "
      comments:
      - number: '21:16 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Within a year, as a servant bound by contract would count
          it. </b>Some ancient manuscripts read <b>Within three years, </b>as in
          16:14.
  - verses:
    - title: A Message about Jerusalem
      content: "  This message came to me concerning Jerusalem\u2014the Valley of
        Vision[[COMMENT(0)]]:What is happening?Why is everyone running to the rooftops?  "
      comments:
      - number: '22:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>concerning the Valley of Vision.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'The whole city is in a terrible uproar.What do I see in this reveling
        city?Bodies are lying everywhere,killed not in battle but by famine and disease.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'All your leaders have fled.They surrendered without resistance.The
        people tried to slip away,but they were captured, too.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "That\u2019s why I said, \u201CLeave me alone to weep;do not try to
        comfort me.Let me cry for my peopleas I watch them being destroyed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Oh, what a day of crushing defeat!What a day of confusion and terrorbrought
        by the Lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,upon
        the Valley of Vision!The walls of Jerusalem have been broken,and cries of
        death echo from the mountainsides.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Elamites are the archers,with their chariots and charioteers.The
        men of Kir hold up the shields.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Chariots fill your beautiful valleys,and charioteers storm your gates.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Judah\u2019s defenses have been stripped away.You run to the armory[[COMMENT(0)]]
        for your weapons.  "
      comments:
      - number: '22:8 '
        content: Hebrew <b>to the House of the Forest; </b>see 1 Kgs 7:2-5.
    - title: 
      content: 'You inspect the breaks in the walls of Jerusalem.[[COMMENT(0)]]You
        store up water in the lower pool.  '
      comments:
      - number: '22:9 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the city of David.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'You survey the houses and tear some downfor stone to strengthen the
        walls.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Between the city walls, you build a reservoirfor water from the old
        pool.But you never ask for help from the One who did all this.You never considered
        the One who planned this long ago.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "At that time the Lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies,called you to weep and mourn.He told you to shave your heads in sorrow
        for your sinsand to wear clothes of burlap to show your remorse.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But instead, you dance and play;you slaughter cattle and kill sheep.You
        feast on meat and drink wine.You say, \u201CLet\u2019s feast and drink,for
        tomorrow we die!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: A Message for Shebna
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies has revealed
        this to me: \u201CTill the day you die, you will never be forgiven for this
        sin.\u201D That is the judgment of the Lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the Lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies, said to me: \u201CConfront Shebna, the palace administrator, and
        give him this message:  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWho do you think you are,and what are you doing here,building
        a beautiful tomb for yourself\u2014a monument high up in the rock?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is about to hurl you away, mighty
        man.He is going to grab you,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'crumple you into a ball,and toss you away into a distant, barren
        land.There you will die,and your glorious chariots will be broken and useless.You
        are a disgrace to your master!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYes, I will drive you out of office,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        \u201CI will pull you down from your high position. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And then I will call my servant Eliakim son of Hilkiah to replace
        you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will dress him in your royal robes and will give him your title
        and your authority. And he will be a father to the people of Jerusalem and
        Judah. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will give him the key to the house of David\u2014the highest position
        in the royal court. When he opens doors, no one will be able to close them;
        when he closes doors, no one will be able to open them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will bring honor to his family name, for I will drive him firmly
        in place like a nail in the wall. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They will give him great responsibility, and he will bring honor
        to even the lowliest members of his family.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '22:24 '
        content: "Hebrew <b>They will hang on him all the glory of his father\u2019s
          house: its offspring and offshoots, all its lesser vessels, from the bowls
          to all the jars.</b>"
  - verses:
    - title: A Message about Tyre
      content: '  This message came to me concerning Tyre:Wail, you trading ships
        of Tarshish,for the harbor and houses of Tyre are gone!The rumors you heard
        in Cyprus[[COMMENT(0)]]are all true.  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Kittim; </b>also in 23:12.
    - title: 
      content: 'Mourn in silence, you people of the coastand you merchants of Sidon.Your
        traders crossed the sea,[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:2 '
        content: As in Dead Sea Scrolls and Greek version; Masoretic Text reads <b>Those
          who have gone over the sea have filled you.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'sailing over deep waters.They brought you grain from Egypt[[COMMENT(0)]]and
        harvests from along the Nile.You were the marketplace of the world.  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:3 '
        content: Hebrew <b>from Shihor, </b>a branch of the Nile River.
    - title: 
      content: "But now you are put to shame, city of Sidon,for Tyre, the fortress
        of the sea, says,[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201CNow I am childless;I have no sons or
        daughters.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:4 '
        content: Or <b>for the god of the sea says; </b>Hebrew reads <b>for the sea,
          the fortress of the sea, says.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'When Egypt hears the news about Tyre,there will be great sorrow.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Send word now to Tarshish!Wail, you people who live in distant lands!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Is this silent ruin all that is left of your once joyous city?What
        a long history was yours!Think of all the colonists you sent to distant places.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Who has brought this disaster on Tyre,that great creator of kingdoms?Her
        traders were all princes,her merchants were nobles.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies has done
        itto destroy your prideand bring low all earth\u2019s nobility.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Come, people of Tarshish,sweep over the land like the flooding Nile,for
        Tyre is defenseless.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:10 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew in this verse is uncertain.
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> held out his hand over the seaand
        shook the kingdoms of the earth.He has spoken out against Phoenicia,[[COMMENT(0)]]ordering
        that her fortresses be destroyed.  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:11 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Canaan.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "He says, \u201CNever again will you rejoice,O daughter of Sidon,
        for you have been crushed.Even if you flee to Cyprus,you will find no rest.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Look at the land of Babylonia[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014the people of that
        land are gone!The Assyrians have handed Babylon overto the wild animals of
        the desert.They have built siege ramps against its walls,torn down its palaces,and
        turned it to a heap of rubble.  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:13 '
        content: Or <b>Chaldea.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Wail, you ships of Tarshish,for your harbor is destroyed!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For seventy years, the length of a king\u2019s life, Tyre will be
        forgotten. But then the city will come back to life as in the song about
        the prostitute:  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Take a harp and walk the streets,you forgotten harlot.Make sweet
        melody and sing your songsso you will be remembered again.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, after seventy years the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will revive
        Tyre. But she will be no different than she was before. She will again be
        a prostitute to all kingdoms around the world. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Destruction of the Earth
      content: '  Look! The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is about to destroy the earthand
        make it a vast wasteland.He devastates the surface of the earthand scatters
        the people.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Priests and laypeople,servants and masters,maids and mistresses,buyers
        and sellers,lenders and borrowers,bankers and debtors\u2014none will be spared.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The earth will be completely emptied and looted.The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has spoken!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The earth mourns and dries up,and the land wastes away and withers.Even
        the greatest people on earth waste away.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The earth suffers for the sins of its people,for they have twisted
        God\u2019s instructions,violated his laws,and broken his everlasting covenant.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Therefore, a curse consumes the earth.Its people must pay the price
        for their sin.They are destroyed by fire,and only a few are left alive.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The grapevines waste away,and there is no new wine.All the merrymakers
        sigh and mourn.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The cheerful sound of tambourines is stilled;the happy cries of celebration
        are heard no more.The melodious chords of the harp are silent.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Gone are the joys of wine and song;alcoholic drink turns bitter in
        the mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The city writhes in chaos;every home is locked to keep out intruders.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Mobs gather in the streets, crying out for wine.Joy has turned to
        gloom.Gladness has been banished from the land.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The city is left in ruins,its gates battered down.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Throughout the earth the story is the same\u2014only a remnant is
        left,like the stray olives left on the treeor the few grapes left on the
        vine after harvest.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But all who are left shout and sing for joy.Those in the west praise
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s majesty.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In eastern lands, give glory to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.In
        the lands beyond the sea, praise the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We hear songs of praise from the ends of the earth,songs that give
        glory to the Righteous One!But my heart is heavy with grief.Weep for me,
        for I wither away.Deceit still prevails,and treachery is everywhere.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Terror and traps and snares will be your lot,you people of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Those who flee in terror will fall into a trap,and those who escape
        the trap will be caught in a snare.Destruction falls like rain from the heavens;the
        foundations of the earth shake.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The earth has broken up.It has utterly collapsed;it is violently
        shaken.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The earth staggers like a drunk.It trembles like a tent in a storm.It
        falls and will not rise again,for the guilt of its rebellion is very heavy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In that day the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will punish the gods
        in the heavensand the proud rulers of the nations on earth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will be rounded up and put in prison.They will be shut up in
        prisonand will finally be punished.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Praise for Judgment and Salvation
      content: '  O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, I will honor and praise your name,for
        you are my God.You do such wonderful things!You planned them long ago,and
        now you have accomplished them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You turn mighty cities into heaps of ruins.Cities with strong walls
        are turned to rubble.Beautiful palaces in distant lands disappearand will
        never be rebuilt.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Therefore, strong nations will declare your glory;ruthless nations
        will fear you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But you are a tower of refuge to the poor, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,a
        tower of refuge to the needy in distress.You are a refuge from the stormand
        a shelter from the heat.For the oppressive acts of ruthless peopleare like
        a storm beating against a wall,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'or like the relentless heat of the desert.But you silence the roar
        of foreign nations.As the shade of a cloud cools relentless heat,so the boastful
        songs of ruthless people are stilled.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In Jerusalem,[[COMMENT(0)]] the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armieswill spread a wonderful feastfor all the people of the world.It will
        be a delicious banquetwith clear, well-aged wine and choice meat.  "
      comments:
      - number: '25:6 '
        content: Hebrew <b>On this mountain; </b>also in 25:10.
    - title: 
      content: 'There he will remove the cloud of gloom,the shadow of death that
        hangs over the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will swallow up death forever!The Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will wipe away all tears.He will remove forever all insults and mockeryagainst
        his land and people.The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has spoken!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In that day the people will proclaim,\u201CThis is our God!We trusted
        in him, and he saved us!This is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, in whom
        we trusted.Let us rejoice in the salvation he brings!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s hand of blessing will
        rest on Jerusalem.But Moab will be crushed.It will be like straw trampled
        down and left to rot.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "God will push down Moab\u2019s peopleas a swimmer pushes down water
        with his hands.He will end their prideand all their evil works.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Song of Praise to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
      content: "  In that day, everyone in the land of Judah will sing this song:Our
        city is strong!We are surrounded by the walls of God\u2019s salvation.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Open the gates to all who are righteous;allow the faithful to enter.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will keep in perfect peaceall who trust in you,all whose thoughts
        are fixed on you!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Trust in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> always,for the <smallcaps>Lord
        God</smallcaps> is the eternal Rock.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He humbles the proudand brings down the arrogant city.He brings it
        down to the dust.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The poor and oppressed trample it underfoot,and the needy walk all
        over it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But for those who are righteous,the way is not steep and rough.You
        are a God who does what is right,and you smooth out the path ahead of them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, we show our trust in you by obeying
        your laws;our heart\u2019s desire is to glorify your name.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In the night I search for you;in the morning[[COMMENT(0)]] I earnestly
        seek you.For only when you come to judge the earthwill people learn what
        is right.  '
      comments:
      - number: '26:9 '
        content: Hebrew <b>within me.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Your kindness to the wickeddoes not make them do good.Although others
        do right, the wicked keep doing wrongand take no notice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        majesty.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, they pay no attention to your upraised
        fist.Show them your eagerness to defend your people.Then they will be ashamed.Let
        your fire consume your enemies.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: '  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, you will grant us peace;all we have
        accomplished is really from you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God, others have ruled us,but you
        alone are the one we worship.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Those we served before are dead and gone.Their departed spirits will
        never return!You attacked them and destroyed them,and they are long forgotten.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, you have made our nation great;yes,
        you have made us great.You have extended our borders,and we give you the
        glory!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: '  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, in distress we searched for you.We
        prayed beneath the burden of your discipline.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Just as a pregnant womanwrithes and cries out in pain as she gives
        birth,so were we in your presence, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We, too, writhe in agony,but nothing comes of our suffering.We have
        not given salvation to the earth,nor brought life into the world.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Restoration for Israel
      content: 'But those who die in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will live;their
        bodies will rise again!Those who sleep in the earthwill rise up and sing
        for joy!For your life-giving light will fall like dewon your people in the
        place of the dead!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Go home, my people,and lock your doors!Hide yourselves for a little
        whileuntil the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s anger has passed.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  In that day the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will take his terrible,
        swift sword and punish Leviathan,[[COMMENT(0)]] the swiftly moving serpent,
        the coiling, writhing serpent. He will kill the dragon of the sea.  '
      comments:
      - number: '27:1 '
        content: The identification of Leviathan is disputed, ranging from an earthly
          creature to a mythical sea monster in ancient literature.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIn that day,sing about the fruitful vineyard.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, will watch over it,watering it
        carefully.Day and night I will watch so no one can harm it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My anger will be gone.If I find briers and thorns growing,I will
        attack them;I will burn them up\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "unless they turn to me for help.Let them make peace with me;yes,
        let them make peace with me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The time is coming when Jacob\u2019s descendants will take root.Israel
        will bud and blossomand fill the whole earth with fruit!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Has the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> struck Israelas he struck her
        enemies?Has he punished heras he punished them?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No, but he exiled Israel to call her to account.She was exiled from
        her landas though blown away in a storm from the east.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> did this to purge Israel\u2019s[[COMMENT(0)]]
        wickedness,to take away all her sin.As a result, all the pagan altars will
        be crushed to dust.No Asherah pole or pagan shrine will be left standing.  "
      comments:
      - number: '27:9 '
        content: "Hebrew <b>Jacob\u2019s. </b>See note on 14:1."
    - title: 
      content: 'The fortified towns will be silent and empty,the houses abandoned,
        the streets overgrown with weeds.Calves will graze there,chewing on twigs
        and branches.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The people are like the dead branches of a tree,broken off and used
        for kindling beneath the cooking pots.Israel is a foolish and stupid nation,for
        its people have turned away from God.Therefore, the one who made themwill
        show them no pity or mercy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yet the time will come when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will
        gather them together like handpicked grain. One by one he will gather them\u2014from
        the Euphrates River[[COMMENT(0)]] in the east to the Brook of Egypt in the
        west. "
      comments:
      - number: '27:12 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the river.</b>
  - verses:
    - title: A Message about Samaria
      content: "  What sorrow awaits the proud city of Samaria\u2014the glorious
        crown of the drunks of Israel.[[COMMENT(0)]]It sits at the head of a fertile
        valley,but its glorious beauty will fade like a flower.It is the pride of
        a peoplebrought down by wine.  "
      comments:
      - number: '28:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>What sorrow awaits the crowning glory of the drunks of
          Ephraim, </b>referring to Samaria, capital of the northern kingdom of Israel.
    - title: 
      content: 'For the Lord will send a mighty army against it.Like a mighty hailstorm
        and a torrential rain,they will burst upon it like a surging floodand smash
        it to the ground.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The proud city of Samaria\u2014the glorious crown of the drunks of
        Israel[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014will be trampled beneath its enemies\u2019 feet.  "
      comments:
      - number: '28:3 '
        content: Hebrew <b>The crowning glory of the drunks of Ephraim; </b>see note
          on 28:1.
    - title: 
      content: 'It sits at the head of a fertile valley,but its glorious beauty will
        fade like a flower.Whoever sees it will snatch it up,as an early fig is quickly
        picked and eaten.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then at last the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armieswill
        himself be Israel\u2019s glorious crown.He will be the pride and joyof the
        remnant of his people.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will give a longing for justiceto their judges.He will give great
        courageto their warriors who stand at the gates.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Now, however, Israel is led by drunkswho reel with wine and stagger
        with alcohol.The priests and prophets stagger with alcoholand lose themselves
        in wine.They reel when they see visionsand stagger as they render decisions.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their tables are covered with vomit;filth is everywhere.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWho does the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> think we are?\u201D
        they ask.\u201CWhy does he speak to us like this?Are we little children,just
        recently weaned?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He tells us everything over and over\u2014one line at a time,one
        line at a time,a little here,and a little there!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So now God will have to speak to his peoplethrough foreign oppressors
        who speak a strange language!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "God has told his people,\u201CHere is a place of rest;let the weary
        rest here.This is a place of quiet rest.\u201DBut they would not listen.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will spell out his message for
        them again,one line at a time,one line at a time,a little here,and a little
        there,so that they will stumble and fall.They will be injured, trapped, and
        captured.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Therefore, listen to this message from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,you
        scoffing rulers in Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You boast, \u201CWe have struck a bargain to cheat deathand have
        made a deal to dodge the grave.[[COMMENT(0)]]The coming destruction can never
        touch us,for we have built a strong refuge made of lies and deception.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '28:15 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Sheol; </b>also in 28:18.
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, this is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says:\u201CLook! I am placing a foundation stone in Jerusalem,[[COMMENT(0)]]a
        firm and tested stone.It is a precious cornerstone that is safe to build
        on.Whoever believes need never be shaken.[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '28:16a '
        content: Hebrew <b>in Zion.</b>
      - number: '28:16b '
        content: Greek version reads <b>Look! I am placing a stone in the foundation
          of Jerusalem </b>[literally <b>Zion</b>], <b>/ a precious cornerstone for
          its foundation, chosen for great honor. / Anyone who trusts in him will
          never be disgraced. </b>Compare Rom 9:33; 1 Pet 2:6.
    - title: 
      content: 'I will test you with the measuring line of justiceand the plumb line
        of righteousness.Since your refuge is made of lies,a hailstorm will knock
        it down.Since it is made of deception,a flood will sweep it away.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will cancel the bargain you made to cheat death,and I will overturn
        your deal to dodge the grave.When the terrible enemy sweeps through,you will
        be trampled into the ground.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Again and again that flood will come,morning after morning,day and
        night,until you are carried away.\u201DThis message will bring terror to
        your people.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The bed you have made is too short to lie on.The blankets are too
        narrow to cover you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will come as he did against the Philistines
        at Mount Perazimand against the Amorites at Gibeon.He will come to do a strange
        thing;he will come to do an unusual deed:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the Lord, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,has
        plainly said that he is determined to crush the whole land.So scoff no more,or
        your punishment will be even greater.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Listen to me;listen, and pay close attention.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Does a farmer always plow and never sow?Is he forever cultivating
        the soil and never planting?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Does he not finally plant his seeds\u2014black cumin, cumin, wheat,
        barley, and emmer wheat\u2014each in its proper way,and each in its proper
        place?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The farmer knows just what to do,for God has given him understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A heavy sledge is never used to thresh black cumin;rather, it is
        beaten with a light stick.A threshing wheel is never rolled on cumin;instead,
        it is beaten lightly with a flail.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Grain for bread is easily crushed,so he doesn\u2019t keep on pounding
        it.He threshes it under the wheels of a cart,but he doesn\u2019t pulverize
        it.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Message about Jerusalem
      content: "  \u201CWhat sorrow awaits Ariel,[[COMMENT(0)]] the City of David.Year
        after year you celebrate your feasts.  "
      comments:
      - number: '29:1 '
        content: "<b>Ariel </b>sounds like a Hebrew term that means \u201Chearth\u201D
          or \u201Caltar.\u201D"
    - title: 
      content: "Yet I will bring disaster upon you,and there will be much weeping
        and sorrow.For Jerusalem will become what her name Ariel means\u2014an altar
        covered with blood.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will be your enemy,surrounding Jerusalem and attacking its walls.I
        will build siege towersand destroy it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then deep from the earth you will speak;from low in the dust your
        words will come.Your voice will whisper from the groundlike a ghost conjured
        up from the grave.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut suddenly, your ruthless enemies will be crushedlike the
        finest of dust.Your many attackers will be driven awaylike chaff before the
        wind.Suddenly, in an instant,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies, will
        act for youwith thunder and earthquake and great noise,with whirlwind and
        storm and consuming fire.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'All the nations fighting against Jerusalem[[COMMENT(0)]]will vanish
        like a dream!Those who are attacking her wallswill vanish like a vision in
        the night.  '
      comments:
      - number: '29:7 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Ariel.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "A hungry person dreams of eatingbut wakes up still hungry.A thirsty
        person dreams of drinkingbut is still faint from thirst when morning comes.So
        it will be with your enemies,with those who attack Mount Zion.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Are you amazed and incredulous?Don\u2019t you believe it?Then go
        ahead and be blind.You are stupid, but not from wine!You stagger, but not
        from liquor!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has poured out on you a spirit
        of deep sleep.He has closed the eyes of your prophets and visionaries.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All the future events in this vision are like a sealed book to them.
        When you give it to those who can read, they will say, \u201CWe can\u2019t
        read it because it is sealed.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When you give it to those who cannot read, they will say, \u201CWe
        don\u2019t know how to read.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And so the Lord says,\u201CThese people say they are mine.They honor
        me with their lips,but their hearts are far from me.And their worship of
        meis nothing but man-made rules learned by rote.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '29:13 '
        content: Greek version reads <b>Their worship is a farce, / for they teach
          man-made ideas as commands from God. </b>Compare Mark 7:7.
    - title: 
      content: "Because of this, I will once again astound these hypocriteswith amazing
        wonders.The wisdom of the wise will pass away,and the intelligence of the
        intelligent will disappear.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "What sorrow awaits those who try to hide their plans from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,who
        do their evil deeds in the dark!\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> can\u2019t
        see us,\u201D they say.\u201CHe doesn\u2019t know what\u2019s going on!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "How foolish can you be?He is the Potter, and he is certainly greater
        than you, the clay!Should the created thing say of the one who made it,\u201CHe
        didn\u2019t make me\u201D?Does a jar ever say,\u201CThe potter who made me
        is stupid\u201D?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Soon\u2014and it will not be very long\u2014the forests of Lebanon
        will become a fertile field,and the fertile field will yield bountiful crops.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In that day the deaf will hear words read from a book,and the blind
        will see through the gloom and darkness.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The humble will be filled with fresh joy from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.The
        poor will rejoice in the Holy One of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The scoffer will be gone,the arrogant will disappear,and those who
        plot evil will be killed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Those who convict the innocentby their false testimony will disappear.A
        similar fate awaits those who use trickery to pervert justiceand who tell
        lies to destroy the innocent.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "That is why the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, who redeemed Abraham,
        says to the people of Israel,[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201CMy people will no longer
        be ashamedor turn pale with fear.  "
      comments:
      - number: '29:22 '
        content: Hebrew <b>of Jacob. </b>See note on 14:1.
    - title: 
      content: 'For when they see their many childrenand all the blessings I have
        given them,they will recognize the holiness of the Holy One of Jacob.They
        will stand in awe of the God of Israel.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Judah\u2019s Worthless Treaty with Egypt"
      content: "  \u201CWhat sorrow awaits my rebellious children,\u201Dsays the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CYou make plans that are contrary to mine.You
        make alliances not directed by my Spirit,thus piling up your sins.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For without consulting me,you have gone down to Egypt for help.You
        have put your trust in Pharaoh\u2019s protection.You have tried to hide in
        his shade.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But by trusting Pharaoh, you will be humiliated,and by depending
        on him, you will be disgraced.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For though his power extends to Zoanand his officials have arrived
        in Hanes,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "all who trust in him will be ashamed.He will not help you.Instead,
        he will disgrace you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This message came to me concerning the animals in the Negev:The caravan
        moves slowlyacross the terrible desert to Egypt\u2014donkeys weighed down
        with richesand camels loaded with treasure\u2014all to pay for Egypt\u2019s
        protection.They travel through the wilderness,a place of lionesses and lions,a
        place where vipers and poisonous snakes live.All this, and Egypt will give
        you nothing in return.  "
      comments: []
    - title: A Warning for Rebellious Judah
      content: "Egypt\u2019s promises are worthless!Therefore, I call her Rahab\u2014the
        Harmless Dragon.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '30:7 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Rahab who sits still. </b>Rahab is the name of a mythical
          sea monster that represents chaos in ancient literature. The name is used
          here as a poetic name for Egypt.
    - title: 
      content: 'Now go and write down these words.Write them in a book.They will
        stand until the end of timeas a witness  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "that these people are stubborn rebelswho refuse to pay attention
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s instructions.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They tell the seers,\u201CStop seeing visions!\u201DThey tell the
        prophets,\u201CDon\u2019t tell us what is right.Tell us nice things.Tell
        us lies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Forget all this gloom.Get off your narrow path.Stop telling us about
        your\u2018Holy One of Israel.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is the reply of the Holy One of Israel:\u201CBecause you despise
        what I tell youand trust instead in oppression and lies,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "calamity will come upon you suddenly\u2014like a bulging wall that
        bursts and falls.In an instant it will collapseand come crashing down.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You will be smashed like a piece of pottery\u2014shattered so completely
        thatthere won\u2019t be a piece big enoughto carry coals from a fireplaceor
        a little water from the well.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,the Holy One
        of Israel, says:\u201COnly in returning to meand resting in me will you be
        saved.In quietness and confidence is your strength.But you would have none
        of it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You said, \u2018No, we will get our help from Egypt.They will give
        us swift horses for riding into battle.\u2019But the only swiftness you are
        going to seeis the swiftness of your enemies chasing you!  "
      comments: []
    - title: "Blessings for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s People"
      content: "One of them will chase a thousand of you.Five of them will make all
        of you flee.You will be left like a lonely flagpole on a hillor a tattered
        banner on a distant mountaintop.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> must wait for you to come to himso
        he can show you his love and compassion.For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is a faithful God.Blessed are those who wait for his help.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O people of Zion, who live in Jerusalem,you will weep no more.He
        will be gracious if you ask for help.He will surely respond to the sound
        of your cries.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Though the Lord gave you adversity for foodand suffering for drink,he
        will still be with you to teach you.You will see your teacher with your own
        eyes.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your own ears will hear him.Right behind you a voice will say,\u201CThis
        is the way you should go,\u201Dwhether to the right or to the left.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then you will destroy all your silver idolsand your precious gold
        images.You will throw them out like filthy rags,saying to them, \u201CGood
        riddance!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will bless you with rain at
        planting time. There will be wonderful harvests and plenty of pastureland
        for your livestock. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The oxen and donkeys that till the ground will eat good grain, its
        chaff blown away by the wind. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In that day, when your enemies are slaughtered and the towers fall,
        there will be streams of water flowing down every mountain and hill. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The moon will be as bright as the sun, and the sun will be seven
        times brighter\u2014like the light of seven days in one! So it will be when
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> begins to heal his people and cure the wounds
        he gave them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Look! The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is coming from far away,burning
        with anger,surrounded by thick, rising smoke.His lips are filled with fury;his
        words consume like fire.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'His hot breath pours out like a floodup to the neck of his enemies.He
        will sift out the proud nations for destruction.He will bridle them and lead
        them away to ruin.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the people of God will sing a song of joy,like the songs at the
        holy festivals.You will be filled with joy,as when a flutist leads a group
        of pilgrimsto Jerusalem, the mountain of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2014to
        the Rock of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will make his majestic voice
        heard.He will display the strength of his mighty arm.It will descend with
        devouring flames,with cloudbursts, thunderstorms, and huge hailstones.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "At the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s command, the Assyrians
        will be shattered.He will strike them down with his royal scepter.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> strikes them with his rod
        of punishment,[[COMMENT(0)]]his people will celebrate with tambourines and
        harps.Lifting his mighty arm, he will fight the Assyrians.  '
      comments:
      - number: '30:32 '
        content: As in some Hebrew manuscripts and Syriac version; Masoretic Text
          reads <b>with the founded rod.</b>
  - verses:
    - title: The Futility of Relying on Egypt
      content: '  What sorrow awaits those who look to Egypt for help,trusting their
        horses, chariots, and charioteersand depending on the strength of human armiesinstead
        of looking to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,the Holy One of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In his wisdom, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will send great disaster;he
        will not change his mind.He will rise against the wickedand against their
        helpers.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For these Egyptians are mere humans, not God!Their horses are puny
        flesh, not mighty spirits!When the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> raises his
        fist against them,those who help will stumble,and those being helped will
        fall.They will all fall down and die together.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has told me:\u201CWhen
        a strong young lionstands growling over a sheep it has killed,it is not frightened
        by the shouts and noiseof a whole crowd of shepherds.In the same way, the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armieswill come down and fight
        on Mount Zion.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies will hover
        over Jerusalemand protect it like a bird protecting its nest.He will defend
        and save the city;he will pass over it and rescue it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Though you are such wicked rebels, my people, come and return to
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I know the glorious day will come when each of you will throw away
        the gold idols and silver images your sinful hands have made.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe Assyrians will be destroyed,but not by the swords of men.The
        sword of God will strike them,and they will panic and flee.The strong young
        Assyrianswill be taken away as captives.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Israel\u2019s Ultimate Deliverance"
      content: '  Look, a righteous king is coming!And honest princes will rule under
        him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Each one will be like a shelter from the windand a refuge from the
        storm,like streams of water in the desertand the shadow of a great rock in
        a parched land.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then everyone who has eyes will be able to see the truth,and everyone
        who has ears will be able to hear it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Even the hotheads will be full of sense and understanding.Those who
        stammer will speak out plainly.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In that day ungodly fools will not be heroes.Scoundrels will not
        be respected.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For fools speak foolishnessand make evil plans.They practice ungodlinessand
        spread false teachings about the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.They deprive
        the hungry of foodand give no water to the thirsty.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The smooth tricks of scoundrels are evil.They plot crooked schemes.They
        lie to convict the poor,even when the cause of the poor is just.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But generous people plan to do what is generous,and they stand firm
        in their generosity.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Listen, you women who lie around in ease.Listen to me, you who are
        so smug.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In a short time\u2014just a little more than a year\u2014you careless
        ones will suddenly begin to care.For your fruit crops will fail,and the harvest
        will never take place.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Tremble, you women of ease;throw off your complacency.Strip off your
        pretty clothes,and put on burlap to show your grief.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Beat your breasts in sorrow for your bountiful farmsand your fruitful
        grapevines.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For your land will be overgrown with thorns and briers.Your joyful
        homes and happy towns will be gone.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The palace and the city will be deserted,and busy towns will be empty.Wild
        donkeys will frolic and flocks will grazein the empty forts[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and watchtowers  '
      comments:
      - number: '32:14 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the Ophel.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'until at last the Spirit is poured outon us from heaven.Then the
        wilderness will become a fertile field,and the fertile field will yield bountiful
        crops.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Justice will rule in the wildernessand righteousness in the fertile
        field.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And this righteousness will bring peace.Yes, it will bring quietness
        and confidence forever.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My people will live in safety, quietly at home.They will be at rest.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Even if the forest should be destroyedand the city torn down,  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Message about Assyria
      content: '  What sorrow awaits you Assyrians, who have destroyed others[[COMMENT(0)]]but
        have never been destroyed yourselves.You betray others,but you have never
        been betrayed.When you are done destroying,you will be destroyed.When you
        are done betraying,you will be betrayed.  '
      comments:
      - number: '33:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>What sorrow awaits you, O destroyer. </b>The Hebrew text
          does not specifically name Assyria as the object of the prophecy in this
          chapter.
    - title: 
      content: 'But <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, be merciful to us,for we have waited
        for you.Be our strong arm each dayand our salvation in times of trouble.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The enemy runs at the sound of your voice.When you stand up, the
        nations flee!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Just as caterpillars and locusts strip the fields and vines,so the
        fallen army of Assyria will be stripped!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Though the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is very great and lives in
        heaven,he will make Jerusalem[[COMMENT(0)]] his home of justice and righteousness.  '
      comments:
      - number: '33:5 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Zion; </b>also in 33:14.
    - title: 
      content: 'In that day he will be your sure foundation,providing a rich store
        of salvation, wisdom, and knowledge.The fear of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will be your treasure.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But now your brave warriors weep in public.Your ambassadors of peace
        cry in bitter disappointment.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your roads are deserted;no one travels them anymore.The Assyrians
        have broken their peace treatyand care nothing for the promises they made
        before witnesses.[[COMMENT(0)]]They have no respect for anyone.  '
      comments:
      - number: '33:8 '
        content: As in Dead Sea Scrolls; Masoretic Text reads <b>care nothing for
          the cities.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'The land of Israel wilts in mourning.Lebanon withers with shame.The
        plain of Sharon is now a wilderness.Bashan and Carmel have been plundered.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: \u201CNow I will stand
        up.Now I will show my power and might.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You Assyrians produce nothing but dry grass and stubble.Your own
        breath will turn to fire and consume you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your people will be burned up completely,like thornbushes cut down
        and tossed in a fire.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Listen to what I have done, you nations far away!And you that are
        near, acknowledge my might!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The sinners in Jerusalem shake with fear.Terror seizes the godless.\u201CWho
        can live with this devouring fire?\u201D they cry.\u201CWho can survive this
        all-consuming fire?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Those who are honest and fair,who refuse to profit by fraud,who stay
        far away from bribes,who refuse to listen to those who plot murder,who shut
        their eyes to all enticement to do wrong\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'these are the ones who will dwell on high.The rocks of the mountains
        will be their fortress.Food will be supplied to them,and they will have water
        in abundance.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your eyes will see the king in all his splendor,and you will see
        a land that stretches into the distance.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You will think back to this time of terror, asking,\u201CWhere are
        the Assyrian officerswho counted our towers?Where are the bookkeeperswho
        recorded the plunder taken from our fallen city?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will no longer see these fierce, violent peoplewith their strange,
        unknown language.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Instead, you will see Zion as a place of holy festivals.You will
        see Jerusalem, a city quiet and secure.It will be like a tent whose ropes
        are tautand whose stakes are firmly fixed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will be our Mighty One.He will be
        like a wide river of protectionthat no enemy can cross,that no enemy ship
        can sail upon.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is our judge,our lawgiver, and
        our king.He will care for us and save us.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The enemies\u2019 sails hang looseon broken masts with useless tackle.Their
        treasure will be divided by the people of God.Even the lame will take their
        share!  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Message for the Nations
      content: '  Come here and listen, O nations of the earth.Let the world and
        everything in it hear my words.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is enraged against the nations.His
        fury is against all their armies.He will completely destroy[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>
        them,</smallcaps>dooming them to slaughter.  '
      comments:
      - number: '34:2 '
        content: The Hebrew term used here refers to the complete consecration of
          things or people to the <span class="ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf">Lord</span>,
          either by destroying them or by giving them as an offering; similarly in
          34:5.
    - title: 
      content: 'Their dead will be left unburied,and the stench of rotting bodies
        will fill the land.The mountains will flow with their blood.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The heavens above will melt awayand disappear like a rolled-up scroll.The
        stars will fall from the skylike withered leaves from a grapevine,or shriveled
        figs from a fig tree.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And when my sword has finished its work in the heavens,it will fall
        upon Edom,the nation I have marked for destruction.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The sword of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is drenched with bloodand
        covered with fat\u2014with the blood of lambs and goats,with the fat of rams
        prepared for sacrifice.Yes, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will offer a
        sacrifice in the city of Bozrah.He will make a mighty slaughter in Edom.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Even men as strong as wild oxen will die\u2014the young men alongside
        the veterans.The land will be soaked with bloodand the soil enriched with
        fat.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For it is the day of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s revenge,the
        year when Edom will be paid back for all it did to Israel.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '34:8 '
        content: Hebrew <b>to Zion.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'The streams of Edom will be filled with burning pitch,and the ground
        will be covered with fire.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This judgment on Edom will never end;the smoke of its burning will
        rise forever.The land will lie deserted from generation to generation.No
        one will live there anymore.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It will be haunted by the desert owl and the screech owl,the great
        owl and the raven.[[COMMENT(0)]]For God will measure that land carefully;he
        will measure it for chaos and destruction.  '
      comments:
      - number: '34:11 '
        content: The identification of some of these birds is uncertain.
    - title: 
      content: 'It will be called the Land of Nothing,and all its nobles will soon
        be gone.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '34:12 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain.
    - title: 
      content: 'Thorns will overrun its palaces;nettles and thistles will grow in
        its forts.The ruins will become a haunt for jackalsand a home for owls.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Desert animals will mingle there with hyenas,their howls filling
        the night.Wild goats will bleat at one another among the ruins,and night
        creatures[[COMMENT(0)]] will come there to rest.  '
      comments:
      - number: '34:14 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Lilith, </b>possibly a reference to a mythical demon of
          the night.
    - title: 
      content: 'There the owl will make her nest and lay her eggs.She will hatch
        her young and cover them with her wings.And the buzzards will come,each one
        with its mate.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Search the book of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and see what he
        will do.Not one of these birds and animals will be missing,and none will
        lack a mate,for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has promised this.His Spirit
        will make it all come true.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Hope for Restoration
      content: '  Even the wilderness and desert will be glad in those days.The wasteland
        will rejoice and blossom with spring crocuses.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, there will be an abundance of flowersand singing and joy!The
        deserts will become as green as the mountains of Lebanon,as lovely as Mount
        Carmel or the plain of Sharon.There the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will
        display his glory,the splendor of our God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'With this news, strengthen those who have tired hands,and encourage
        those who have weak knees.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Say to those with fearful hearts,\u201CBe strong, and do not fear,for
        your God is coming to destroy your enemies.He is coming to save you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And when he comes, he will open the eyes of the blindand unplug the
        ears of the deaf.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The lame will leap like a deer,and those who cannot speak will sing
        for joy!Springs will gush forth in the wilderness,and streams will water
        the wasteland.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The parched ground will become a pool,and springs of water will satisfy
        the thirsty land.Marsh grass and reeds and rushes will flourishwhere desert
        jackals once lived.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And a great road will go through that once deserted land.It will
        be named the Highway of Holiness.Evil-minded people will never travel on
        it.It will be only for those who walk in God\u2019s ways;fools will never
        walk there.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Lions will not lurk along its course,nor any other ferocious beasts.There
        will be no other dangers.Only the redeemed will walk on it.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Assyria Invades Judah
      content: "  In the fourteenth year of King Hezekiah\u2019s reign,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        King Sennacherib of Assyria came to attack the fortified towns of Judah and
        conquered them. "
      comments:
      - number: '36:1 '
        content: "The fourteenth year of Hezekiah\u2019s reign was 701 <span class=\"ChapterContent_sc__Hg9da\">b.c.</span>"
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the king of Assyria sent his chief of staff[[COMMENT(0)]] from
        Lachish with a huge army to confront King Hezekiah in Jerusalem. The Assyrians
        took up a position beside the aqueduct that feeds water into the upper pool,
        near the road leading to the field where cloth is washed.[[COMMENT(1)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '36:2a '
        content: Or <b>the rabshakeh; </b>also in 36:4, 11, 12, 22.
      - number: '36:2b '
        content: Or <b>bleached.</b>
    - title: Sennacherib Threatens Jerusalem
      content: 'These are the officials who went out to meet with them: Eliakim son
        of Hilkiah, the palace administrator; Shebna the court secretary; and Joah
        son of Asaph, the royal historian.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the Assyrian king\u2019s chief of staff told them to give this
        message to Hezekiah:\u201CThis is what the great king of Assyria says: What
        are you trusting in that makes you so confident? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do you think[[COMMENT(0)]] that mere words can substitute for military
        skill and strength? Who are you counting on, that you have rebelled against
        me? '
      comments:
      - number: '36:5 '
        content: As in Dead Sea Scrolls (see also 2 Kgs 18:20); Masoretic Text reads
          <b>Do I think.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'On Egypt? If you lean on Egypt, it will be like a reed that splinters
        beneath your weight and pierces your hand. Pharaoh, the king of Egypt, is
        completely unreliable!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut perhaps you will say to me, \u2018We are trusting in the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God!\u2019 But isn\u2019t he the one who
        was insulted by Hezekiah? Didn\u2019t Hezekiah tear down his shrines and
        altars and make everyone in Judah and Jerusalem worship only at the altar
        here in Jerusalem?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI\u2019ll tell you what! Strike a bargain with my master, the
        king of Assyria. I will give you 2,000 horses if you can find that many men
        to ride on them! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "With your tiny army, how can you think of challenging even the weakest
        contingent of my master\u2019s troops, even with the help of Egypt\u2019s
        chariots and charioteers? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "What\u2019s more, do you think we have invaded your land without
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s direction? The <smallcaps>Lord </smallcaps>himself
        told us, \u2018Attack this land and destroy it!\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Eliakim, Shebna, and Joah said to the Assyrian chief of staff,
        \u201CPlease speak to us in Aramaic, for we understand it well. Don\u2019t
        speak in Hebrew,[[COMMENT(0)]] for the people on the wall will hear.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '36:11 '
        content: Hebrew <b>in the dialect of Judah; </b>also in 36:13.
    - title: 
      content: "But Sennacherib\u2019s chief of staff replied, \u201CDo you think
        my master sent this message only to you and your master? He wants all the
        people to hear it, for when we put this city under siege, they will suffer
        along with you. They will be so hungry and thirsty that they will eat their
        own dung and drink their own urine.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the chief of staff stood and shouted in Hebrew to the people
        on the wall, \u201CListen to this message from the great king of Assyria! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the king says: Don\u2019t let Hezekiah deceive you.
        He will never be able to rescue you. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t let him fool you into trusting in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        by saying, \u2018The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will surely rescue us. This
        city will never fall into the hands of the Assyrian king!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CDon\u2019t listen to Hezekiah! These are the terms the king
        of Assyria is offering: Make peace with me\u2014open the gates and come out.
        Then each of you can continue eating from your own grapevine and fig tree
        and drinking from your own well. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then I will arrange to take you to another land like this one\u2014a
        land of grain and new wine, bread and vineyards.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CDon\u2019t let Hezekiah mislead you by saying, \u2018The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will rescue us!\u2019 Have the gods of any other nations ever saved their
        people from the king of Assyria? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'What happened to the gods of Hamath and Arpad? And what about the
        gods of Sepharvaim? Did any god rescue Samaria from my power? '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "What god of any nation has ever been able to save its people from
        my power? So what makes you think that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> can
        rescue Jerusalem from me?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the people were silent and did not utter a word because Hezekiah
        had commanded them, \u201CDo not answer him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Hezekiah Seeks the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Help"
      content: '  When King Hezekiah heard their report, he tore his clothes and
        put on burlap and went into the Temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And he sent Eliakim the palace administrator, Shebna the court secretary,
        and the leading priests, all dressed in burlap, to the prophet Isaiah son
        of Amoz. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They told him, \u201CThis is what King Hezekiah says: Today is a
        day of trouble, insults, and disgrace. It is like when a child is ready to
        be born, but the mother has no strength to deliver the baby. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But perhaps the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God has heard the
        Assyrian chief of staff,[[COMMENT(0)]] sent by the king to defy the living
        God, and will punish him for his words. Oh, pray for those of us who are
        left!\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '37:4 '
        content: Or <b>the rabshakeh; </b>also in 37:8.
    - title: 
      content: "After King Hezekiah\u2019s officials delivered the king\u2019s message
        to Isaiah, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "the prophet replied, \u201CSay to your master, \u2018This is what
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: Do not be disturbed by this blasphemous
        speech against me from the Assyrian king\u2019s messengers. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Listen! I myself will move against him,[[COMMENT(0)]] and the king
        will receive a message that he is needed at home. So he will return to his
        land, where I will have him killed with a sword.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '37:7 '
        content: Hebrew <b>I will put a spirit in him.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Meanwhile, the Assyrian chief of staff left Jerusalem and went to
        consult the king of Assyria, who had left Lachish and was attacking Libnah.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Soon afterward King Sennacherib received word that King Tirhakah
        of Ethiopia[[COMMENT(0)]] was leading an army to fight against him. Before
        leaving to meet the attack, he sent messengers back to Hezekiah in Jerusalem
        with this message:  '
      comments:
      - number: '37:9 '
        content: Hebrew <b>of Cush.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThis message is for King Hezekiah of Judah. Don\u2019t let
        your God, in whom you trust, deceive you with promises that Jerusalem will
        not be captured by the king of Assyria. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You know perfectly well what the kings of Assyria have done wherever
        they have gone. They have completely destroyed everyone who stood in their
        way! Why should you be any different? '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Have the gods of other nations rescued them\u2014such nations as
        Gozan, Haran, Rezeph, and the people of Eden who were in Tel-assar? My predecessors
        destroyed them all! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "What happened to the king of Hamath and the king of Arpad? What happened
        to the kings of Sepharvaim, Hena, and Ivvah?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "After Hezekiah received the letter from the messengers and read it,
        he went up to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Temple and spread it
        out before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And Hezekiah prayed this prayer before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CO <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies, God
        of Israel, you are enthroned between the mighty cherubim! You alone are God
        of all the kingdoms of the earth. You alone created the heavens and the earth. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Bend down, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and listen! Open your eyes,
        O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and see! Listen to Sennacherib\u2019s words
        of defiance against the living God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIt is true, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, that the kings of
        Assyria have destroyed all these nations. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And they have thrown the gods of these nations into the fire and
        burned them. But of course the Assyrians could destroy them! They were not
        gods at all\u2014only idols of wood and stone shaped by human hands. "
      comments: []
    - title: "Isaiah Predicts Judah\u2019s Deliverance"
      content: "Now, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God, rescue us from his power;
        then all the kingdoms of the earth will know that you alone, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        are God.[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>\u201D</smallcaps>  "
      comments:
      - number: '37:20 '
        content: As in Dead Sea Scrolls (see also 2 Kgs 19:19); Masoretic Text reads
          <b>you alone are the <span class="ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf">Lord</span>.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Then Isaiah son of Amoz sent this message to Hezekiah: \u201CThis
        is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel, says: Because
        you prayed about King Sennacherib of Assyria, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has spoken this word against him:\u201CThe
        virgin daughter of Ziondespises you and laughs at you.The daughter of Jerusalemshakes
        her head in derision as you flee.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhom have you been defying and ridiculing?Against whom did
        you raise your voice?At whom did you look with such haughty eyes?It was the
        Holy One of Israel!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "By your messengers you have defied the Lord.You have said, \u2018With
        my many chariotsI have conquered the highest mountains\u2014yes, the remotest
        peaks of Lebanon.I have cut down its tallest cedarsand its finest cypress
        trees.I have reached its farthest heightsand explored its deepest forests.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I have dug wells in many foreign lands[[COMMENT(0)]]and refreshed
        myself with their water.With the sole of my foot,I stopped up all the rivers
        of Egypt!\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '37:25 '
        content: As in Dead Sea Scrolls (see also 2 Kgs 19:24); Masoretic Text lacks
          <b>in many foreign lands.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut have you not heard?I decided this long ago.Long ago I planned
        it,and now I am making it happen.I planned for you to crush fortified citiesinto
        heaps of rubble.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'That is why their people have so little powerand are so frightened
        and confused.They are as weak as grass,as easily trampled as tender green
        shoots.They are like grass sprouting on a housetop,scorched[[COMMENT(0)]]
        before it can grow lush and tall.  '
      comments:
      - number: '37:27 '
        content: As in Dead Sea Scrolls and some Greek manuscripts (see also 2 Kgs
          19:26); most Hebrew manuscripts read <b>like a terraced field.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut I know you well\u2014where you stayand when you come and
        go.I know the way you have raged against me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And because of your raging against meand your arrogance, which I
        have heard for myself,I will put my hook in your noseand my bit in your mouth.I
        will make you returnby the same road on which you came.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Isaiah said to Hezekiah, \u201CHere is the proof that what I
        say is true:\u201CThis year you will eat only what grows up by itself,and
        next year you will eat what springs up from that.But in the third year you
        will plant crops and harvest them;you will tend vineyards and eat their fruit.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And you who are left in Judah,who have escaped the ravages of the
        siege,will put roots down in your own soiland grow up and flourish.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For a remnant of my people will spread out from Jerusalem,a group
        of survivors from Mount Zion.The passionate commitment of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armieswill make this happen!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAnd this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says about
        the king of Assyria:\u201C\u2018His armies will not enter Jerusalem.They
        will not even shoot an arrow at it.They will not march outside its gates
        with their shieldsnor build banks of earth against its walls.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The king will return to his own countryby the same road on which
        he came.He will not enter this city,\u2019says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018For my own honor and for the sake of my servant David,I will
        defend this city and protect it.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'That night the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> went out
        to the Assyrian camp and killed 185,000 Assyrian soldiers. When the surviving
        Assyrians[[COMMENT(0)]] woke up the next morning, they found corpses everywhere. '
      comments:
      - number: '37:36 '
        content: Hebrew <b>When they.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Then King Sennacherib of Assyria broke camp and returned to his own
        land. He went home to his capital of Nineveh and stayed there.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Hezekiah\u2019s Sickness and Recovery"
      content: "  About that time Hezekiah became deathly ill, and the prophet Isaiah
        son of Amoz went to visit him. He gave the king this message: \u201CThis
        is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: \u2018Set your affairs in order,
        for you are going to die. You will not recover from this illness.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When Hezekiah heard this, he turned his face to the wall and prayed
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CRemember, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, how I have always
        been faithful to you and have served you single-mindedly, always doing what
        pleases you.\u201D Then he broke down and wept bitterly.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then this message came to Isaiah from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGo back to Hezekiah and tell him, \u2018This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of your ancestor David, says: I have heard your prayer and seen your
        tears. I will add fifteen years to your life, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and I will rescue you and this city from the king of Assyria. Yes,
        I will defend this city.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201C\u2018And this is the sign from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        to prove that he will do as he promised: "
      comments: []
    - title: "Hezekiah\u2019s Poem of Praise"
      content: "I will cause the sun\u2019s shadow to move ten steps backward on
        the sundial[[COMMENT(0)]] of Ahaz!\u2019\u201D So the shadow on the sundial
        moved backward ten steps.  "
      comments:
      - number: '38:8 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the steps.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'When King Hezekiah was well again, he wrote this poem:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I said, \u201CIn the prime of my life,must I now enter the place
        of the dead?[[COMMENT(0)]]Am I to be robbed of the rest of my years?\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '38:10 '
        content: Hebrew <b>enter the gates of Sheol?</b>
    - title: 
      content: "I said, \u201CNever again will I see the <smallcaps>Lord God</smallcaps>while
        still in the land of the living.Never again will I see my friendsor be with
        those who live in this world.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My life has been blown awaylike a shepherd\u2019s tent in a storm.It
        has been cut short,as when a weaver cuts cloth from a loom.Suddenly, my life
        was over.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I waited patiently all night,but I was torn apart as though by lions.Suddenly,
        my life was over.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Delirious, I chattered like a swallow or a crane,and then I moaned
        like a mourning dove.My eyes grew tired of looking to heaven for help.I am
        in trouble, Lord. Help me!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But what could I say?For he himself sent this sickness.Now I will
        walk humbly throughout my yearsbecause of this anguish I have felt.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Lord, your discipline is good,for it leads to life and health.You
        restore my healthand allow me to live!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, this anguish was good for me,for you have rescued me from deathand
        forgiven all my sins.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the dead[[COMMENT(0)]] cannot praise you;they cannot raise their
        voices in praise.Those who go down to the gravecan no longer hope in your
        faithfulness.  '
      comments:
      - number: '38:18 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Sheol.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Only the living can praise you as I do today.Each generation tells
        of your faithfulness to the next.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Think of it\u2014the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is ready to heal
        me!I will sing his praises with instrumentsevery day of my lifein the Temple
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Isaiah had said to Hezekiah\u2019s servants, \u201CMake an ointment
        from figs and spread it over the boil, and Hezekiah will recover.\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Envoys from Babylon
      content: '  Soon after this, Merodach-baladan son of Baladan, king of Babylon,
        sent Hezekiah his best wishes and a gift. He had heard that Hezekiah had
        been very sick and that he had recovered. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Hezekiah was delighted with the Babylonian envoys and showed them
        everything in his treasure-houses\u2014the silver, the gold, the spices,
        and the aromatic oils. He also took them to see his armory and showed them
        everything in his royal treasuries! There was nothing in his palace or kingdom
        that Hezekiah did not show them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Isaiah the prophet went to King Hezekiah and asked him, \u201CWhat
        did those men want? Where were they from?\u201DHezekiah replied, \u201CThey
        came from the distant land of Babylon.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhat did they see in your palace?\u201D asked Isaiah.\u201CThey
        saw everything,\u201D Hezekiah replied. \u201CI showed them everything I
        own\u2014all my royal treasuries.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Isaiah said to Hezekiah, \u201CListen to this message from the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies: "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018The time is coming when everything in your palace\u2014all
        the treasures stored up by your ancestors until now\u2014will be carried
        off to Babylon. Nothing will be left,\u2019 says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018Some of your very own sons will be taken away into exile. They
        will become eunuchs who will serve in the palace of Babylon\u2019s king.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Comfort for God\u2019s People"
      content: "  \u201CComfort, comfort my people,\u201Dsays your God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSpeak tenderly to Jerusalem.Tell her that her sad days are
        goneand her sins are pardoned.Yes, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has punished
        her twice overfor all her sins.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Listen! It\u2019s the voice of someone shouting,\u201CClear the way
        through the wildernessfor the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!Make a straight
        highway through the wastelandfor our God!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Fill in the valleys,and level the mountains and hills.Straighten
        the curves,and smooth out the rough places.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the glory of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will be revealed,and
        all people will see it together.The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has spoken!\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps><smallcaps>Compare
        Matt 3:3; Mark 1:3; Luke 3:4-6.</smallcaps>  "
      comments:
      - number: '40:3-5 '
        content: "Greek version reads <b>He is a voice shouting in the wilderness,
          / \u201CPrepare the way for the <span class=\"ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf\">Lord</span>\u2019s
          coming! / Clear a road for our God! / Fill in the valleys, / and level
          the mountains and hills. / And then the glory of the <span class=\"ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf\">Lord</span>
          will be revealed, / and all people will see the salvation sent from God.
          / The <span class=\"ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf\">Lord</span> has spoken!\u201D
          </b>"
    - title: 
      content: "A voice said, \u201CShout!\u201DI asked, \u201CWhat should I shout?\u201D\u201CShout
        that people are like the grass.Their beauty fades as quicklyas the flowers
        in a field.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The grass withers and the flowers fadebeneath the breath of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.And
        so it is with people.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The grass withers and the flowers fade,but the word of our God stands
        forever.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "O Zion, messenger of good news,shout from the mountaintops!Shout
        it louder, O Jerusalem.[[COMMENT(0)]]Shout, and do not be afraid.Tell the
        towns of Judah,\u201CYour God is coming!\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '40:9 '
        content: Or <b>O messenger of good news, shout to Zion from the mountaintops!
          Shout it louder to Jerusalem.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is coming in power.He
        will rule with a powerful arm.See, he brings his reward with him as he comes.  '
      comments: []
    - title: The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> Has No Equal
      content: 'He will feed his flock like a shepherd.He will carry the lambs in
        his arms,holding them close to his heart.He will gently lead the mother sheep
        with their young.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Who else has held the oceans in his hand?Who has measured off the
        heavens with his fingers?Who else knows the weight of the earthor has weighed
        the mountains and hills on a scale?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Who is able to advise the Spirit of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>Compare
        Rom 11:34; 1 Cor 2:16.</smallcaps>Who knows enough to give him advice or
        teach him?  '
      comments:
      - number: '40:13 '
        content: "Greek version reads <b>Who can know the <span class=\"ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf\">Lord</span>\u2019s
          thoughts? </b>"
    - title: 
      content: "Has the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> ever needed anyone\u2019s advice?Does
        he need instruction about what is good?Did someone teach him what is rightor
        show him the path of justice?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No, for all the nations of the worldare but a drop in the bucket.They
        are nothing morethan dust on the scales.He picks up the whole earthas though
        it were a grain of sand.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All the wood in Lebanon\u2019s forestsand all Lebanon\u2019s animals
        would not be enoughto make a burnt offering worthy of our God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The nations of the world are worth nothing to him.In his eyes they
        count for less than nothing\u2014mere emptiness and froth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'To whom can you compare God?What image can you find to resemble him?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Can he be compared to an idol formed in a mold,overlaid with gold,
        and decorated with silver chains?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Or if people are too poor for that,they might at least choose wood
        that won\u2019t decayand a skilled craftsmanto carve an image that won\u2019t
        fall down!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Haven\u2019t you heard? Don\u2019t you understand?Are you deaf to
        the words of God\u2014the words he gave before the world began?Are you so
        ignorant?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'God sits above the circle of the earth.The people below seem like
        grasshoppers to him!He spreads out the heavens like a curtainand makes his
        tent from them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He judges the great people of the worldand brings them all to nothing.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They hardly get started, barely taking root,when he blows on them
        and they wither.The wind carries them off like chaff.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTo whom will you compare me?Who is my equal?\u201D asks the
        Holy One.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Look up into the heavens.Who created all the stars?He brings them
        out like an army, one after another,calling each by its name.Because of his
        great power and incomparable strength,not a single one is missing.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O Jacob, how can you say the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> does not
        see your troubles?O Israel, how can you say God ignores your rights?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Have you never heard?Have you never understood?The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is the everlasting God,the Creator of all the earth.He never grows weak or
        weary.No one can measure the depths of his understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He gives power to the weakand strength to the powerless.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Even youths will become weak and tired,and young men will fall in
        exhaustion.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "God\u2019s Help for Israel"
      content: "  \u201CListen in silence before me, you lands beyond the sea.Bring
        your strongest arguments.Come now and speak.The court is ready for your case.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWho has stirred up this king from the east,rightly calling
        him to God\u2019s service?Who gives this man victory over many nationsand
        permits him to trample their kings underfoot?With his sword, he reduces armies
        to dust.With his bow, he scatters them like chaff before the wind.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He chases them away and goes on safely,though he is walking over
        unfamiliar ground.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Who has done such mighty deeds,summoning each new generation from
        the beginning of time?It is I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the First
        and the Last.I alone am he.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The lands beyond the sea watch in fear.Remote lands tremble and mobilize
        for war.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The idol makers encourage one another,saying to each other, \u201CBe
        strong!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The carver encourages the goldsmith,and the molder helps at the anvil.\u201CGood,\u201D
        they say. \u201CIt\u2019s coming along fine.\u201DCarefully they join the
        parts together,then fasten the thing in place so it won\u2019t fall over.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut as for you, Israel my servant,Jacob my chosen one,descended
        from Abraham my friend,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I have called you back from the ends of the earth,saying, \u2018You
        are my servant.\u2019For I have chosen youand will not throw you away.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t be afraid, for I am with you.Don\u2019t be discouraged,
        for I am your God.I will strengthen you and help you.I will hold you up with
        my victorious right hand.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSee, all your angry enemies lie there,confused and humiliated.Anyone
        who opposes you will dieand come to nothing.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will look in vainfor those who tried to conquer you.Those who
        attack youwill come to nothing.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I hold you by your right hand\u2014I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God.And I say to you,\u2018Don\u2019t be afraid. I am here to help you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Though you are a lowly worm, O Jacob,don\u2019t be afraid, people
        of Israel, for I will help you.I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, your
        Redeemer.I am the Holy One of Israel.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will be a new threshing instrumentwith many sharp teeth.You will
        tear your enemies apart,making chaff of mountains.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will toss them into the air,and the wind will blow them all away;a
        whirlwind will scatter them.Then you will rejoice in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.You
        will glory in the Holy One of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen the poor and needy search for water and there is none,and
        their tongues are parched from thirst,then I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        will answer them.I, the God of Israel, will never abandon them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will open up rivers for them on the high plateaus.I will give them
        fountains of water in the valleys.I will fill the desert with pools of water.Rivers
        fed by springs will flow across the parched ground.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will plant trees in the barren desert\u2014cedar, acacia, myrtle,
        olive, cypress, fir, and pine.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I am doing this so all who see this miraclewill understand what it
        means\u2014that it is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> who has done this,the
        Holy One of Israel who created it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CPresent the case for your idols,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CLet
        them show what they can do,\u201Dsays the King of Israel.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '41:21 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the King of Jacob. </b>See note on 14:1.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CLet them try to tell us what happened long agoso that we may
        consider the evidence.Or let them tell us what the future holds,so we can
        know what\u2019s going to happen.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yes, tell us what will occur in the days ahead.Then we will know
        you are gods.In fact, do anything\u2014good or bad!Do something that will
        amaze and frighten us.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But no! You are less than nothing and can do nothing at all.Those
        who choose you pollute themselves.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut I have stirred up a leader who will approach from the north.From
        the east he will call on my name.I will give him victory over kings and princes.He
        will trample them as a potter treads on clay.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWho told you from the beginningthat this would happen?Who predicted
        this,making you admit that he was right?No one said a word!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I was the first to tell Zion,\u2018Look! Help is on the way!\u2019[[COMMENT(0)]]I
        will send Jerusalem a messenger with good news.  "
      comments:
      - number: '41:27 '
        content: "Or <b>\u2018Look! They are coming home.\u2019</b>"
    - title: 
      content: 'Not one of your idols told you this.Not one gave any answer when
        I asked.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Chosen Servant"
      content: "  \u201CLook at my servant, whom I strengthen.He is my chosen one,
        who pleases me.I have put my Spirit upon him.He will bring justice to the
        nations.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will not shoutor raise his voice in public.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will not crush the weakest reedor put out a flickering candle.He
        will bring justice to all who have been wronged.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He will not falter or lose heartuntil justice prevails throughout
        the earth.Even distant lands beyond the sea will wait for his instruction.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '42:4 '
        content: Greek version reads <b>And his name will be the hope of all the
          world. </b>Compare Matt 12:21.
    - title: 
      content: 'God, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, created the heavens and stretched
        them out.He created the earth and everything in it.He gives breath to everyone,life
        to everyone who walks the earth.And it is he who says,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have called you to demonstrate
        my righteousness.I will take you by the hand and guard you,and I will give
        you to my people, Israel,as a symbol of my covenant with them.And you will
        be a light to guide the nations.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will open the eyes of the blind.You will free the captives from
        prison,releasing those who sit in dark dungeons.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>; that is my name!I will
        not give my glory to anyone else,nor share my praise with carved idols.  "
      comments: []
    - title: A Song of Praise to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
      content: "Everything I prophesied has come true,and now I will prophesy again.I
        will tell you the future before it happens.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Sing a new song to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!Sing his praises
        from the ends of the earth!Sing, all you who sail the seas,all you who live
        in distant coastlands.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Join in the chorus, you desert towns;let the villages of Kedar rejoice!Let
        the people of Sela sing for joy;shout praises from the mountaintops!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let the whole world glorify the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;let it
        sing his praise.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will march forth like a mighty hero;he
        will come out like a warrior, full of fury.He will shout his battle cryand
        crush all his enemies.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He will say, \u201CI have long been silent;yes, I have restrained
        myself.But now, like a woman in labor,I will cry and groan and pant.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will level the mountains and hillsand blight all their greenery.I
        will turn the rivers into dry landand will dry up all the pools.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will lead blind Israel down a new path,guiding them along an unfamiliar
        way.I will brighten the darkness before themand smooth out the road ahead
        of them.Yes, I will indeed do these things;I will not forsake them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: "Israel\u2019s Failure to Listen and See"
      content: "But those who trust in idols,who say, \u2018You are our gods,\u2019will
        be turned away in shame.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CListen, you who are deaf!Look and see, you blind!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Who is as blind as my own people, my servant?Who is as deaf as my
        messenger?Who is as blind as my chosen people,the servant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You see and recognize what is rightbut refuse to act on it.You hear
        with your ears,but you don\u2019t really listen.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Because he is righteous,the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has exalted
        his glorious law.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But his own people have been robbed and plundered,enslaved, imprisoned,
        and trapped.They are fair game for anyoneand have no one to protect them,no
        one to take them back home.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Who will hear these lessons from the pastand see the ruin that awaits
        you in the future?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Who allowed Israel to be robbed and hurt?It was the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        against whom we sinned,for the people would not walk in his path,nor would
        they obey his law.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Savior of Israel
      content: "  But now, O Jacob, listen to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> who
        created you.O Israel, the one who formed you says,\u201CDo not be afraid,
        for I have ransomed you.I have called you by name; you are mine.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When you go through deep waters,I will be with you.When you go through
        rivers of difficulty,you will not drown.When you walk through the fire of
        oppression,you will not be burned up;the flames will not consume you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, your God,the Holy One of
        Israel, your Savior.I gave Egypt as a ransom for your freedom;I gave Ethiopia[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and Seba in your place.  '
      comments:
      - number: '43:3 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Cush.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Others were given in exchange for you.I traded their lives for yoursbecause
        you are precious to me.You are honored, and I love you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CDo not be afraid, for I am with you.I will gather you and your
        children from east and west.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will say to the north and south,\u2018Bring my sons and daughters
        back to Israelfrom the distant corners of the earth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Bring all who claim me as their God,for I have made them for my glory.It
        was I who created them.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Bring out the people who have eyes but are blind,who have ears but
        are deaf.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Gather the nations together!Assemble the peoples of the world!Which
        of their idols has ever foretold such things?Which can predict what will
        happen tomorrow?Where are the witnesses of such predictions?Who can verify
        that they spoke the truth?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut you are my witnesses, O Israel!\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CYou
        are my servant.You have been chosen to know me, believe in me,and understand
        that I alone am God.There is no other God\u2014there never has been, and
        there never will be.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I, yes I, am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and there is no other
        Savior.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "First I predicted your rescue,then I saved you and proclaimed it
        to the world.No foreign god has ever done this.You are witnesses that I am
        the only God,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - title: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Promise of Victory"
      content: "\u201CFrom eternity to eternity I am God.No one can snatch anyone
        out of my hand.No one can undo what I have done.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says\u2014your Redeemer,
        the Holy One of Israel:\u201CFor your sakes I will send an army against Babylon,forcing
        the Babylonians[[COMMENT(0)]] to flee in those ships they are so proud of.  "
      comments:
      - number: '43:14 '
        content: Or <b>Chaldeans.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, your Holy One,Israel\u2019s
        Creator and King.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, who opened a way through the
        waters,making a dry path through the sea.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I called forth the mighty army of Egyptwith all its chariots and
        horses.I drew them beneath the waves, and they drowned,their lives snuffed
        out like a smoldering candlewick.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut forget all that\u2014it is nothing compared to what I am
        going to do.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For I am about to do something new.See, I have already begun! Do
        you not see it?I will make a pathway through the wilderness.I will create
        rivers in the dry wasteland.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The wild animals in the fields will thank me,the jackals and owls,
        too,for giving them water in the desert.Yes, I will make rivers in the dry
        wastelandso my chosen people can be refreshed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I have made Israel for myself,and they will someday honor me before
        the whole world.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut, dear family of Jacob, you refuse to ask for my help.You
        have grown tired of me, O Israel!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have not brought me sheep or goats for burnt offerings.You have
        not honored me with sacrifices,though I have not burdened and wearied youwith
        requests for grain offerings and frankincense.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have not brought me fragrant calamusor pleased me with the fat
        from sacrifices.Instead, you have burdened me with your sinsand wearied me
        with your faults.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI\u2014yes, I alone\u2014will blot out your sins for my own
        sakeand will never think of them again.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let us review the situation together,and you can present your case
        to prove your innocence.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'From the very beginning, your first ancestor sinned against me;all
        your leaders broke my laws.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CBut now, listen to me, Jacob my servant,Israel my chosen
        one.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> who made you and helps you says:Do
        not be afraid, O Jacob, my servant,O dear Israel,[[COMMENT(0)]] my chosen
        one.  '
      comments:
      - number: '44:2 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Jeshurun, </b>a term of endearment for Israel.
    - title: 
      content: 'For I will pour out water to quench your thirstand to irrigate your
        parched fields.And I will pour out my Spirit on your descendants,and my blessing
        on your children.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will thrive like watered grass,like willows on a riverbank.  '
      comments: []
    - title: The Foolishness of Idols
      content: "Some will proudly claim, \u2018I belong to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u2019Others
        will say, \u2018I am a descendant of Jacob.\u2019Some will write the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        name on their handsand will take the name of Israel as their own.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says\u2014Israel\u2019s
        King and Redeemer, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies:\u201CI
        am the First and the Last;there is no other God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Who is like me?Let him step forward and prove to you his power.Let
        him do as I have done since ancient timeswhen I established a people and
        explained its future.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Do not tremble; do not be afraid.Did I not proclaim my purposes for
        you long ago?You are my witnesses\u2014is there any other God?No! There is
        no other Rock\u2014not one!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "How foolish are those who manufacture idols.These prized objects
        are really worthless.The people who worship idols don\u2019t know this,so
        they are all put to shame.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Who but a fool would make his own god\u2014an idol that cannot help
        him one bit?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All who worship idols will be disgracedalong with all these craftsmen\u2014mere
        humans\u2014who claim they can make a god.They may all stand together,but
        they will stand in terror and shame.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The blacksmith stands at his forge to make a sharp tool,pounding
        and shaping it with all his might.His work makes him hungry and weak.It makes
        him thirsty and faint.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the wood-carver measures a block of woodand draws a pattern
        on it.He works with chisel and planeand carves it into a human figure.He
        gives it human beautyand puts it in a little shrine.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He cuts down cedars;he selects the cypress and the oak;he plants
        the pine in the forestto be nourished by the rain.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then he uses part of the wood to make a fire.With it he warms himself
        and bakes his bread.Then\u2014yes, it\u2019s true\u2014he takes the rest
        of itand makes himself a god to worship!He makes an idoland bows down in
        front of it!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He burns part of the tree to roast his meatand to keep himself warm.He
        says, \u201CAh, that fire feels good.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then he takes what\u2019s leftand makes his god: a carved idol!He
        falls down in front of it,worshiping and praying to it.\u201CRescue me!\u201D
        he says.\u201CYou are my god!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Such stupidity and ignorance!Their eyes are closed, and they cannot
        see.Their minds are shut, and they cannot think.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The person who made the idol never stops to reflect,\u201CWhy, it\u2019s
        just a block of wood!I burned half of it for heatand used it to bake my bread
        and roast my meat.How can the rest of it be a god?Should I bow down to worship
        a piece of wood?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Restoration for Jerusalem
      content: "The poor, deluded fool feeds on ashes.He trusts something that can\u2019t
        help him at all.Yet he cannot bring himself to ask,\u201CIs this idol that
        I\u2019m holding in my hand a lie?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CPay attention, O Jacob,for you are my servant, O Israel.I,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, made you,and I will not forget you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I have swept away your sins like a cloud.I have scattered your offenses
        like the morning mist.Oh, return to me,for I have paid the price to set you
        free.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Sing, O heavens, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has done this
        wondrous thing.Shout for joy, O depths of the earth!Break into song,O mountains
        and forests and every tree!For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has redeemed
        Jacoband is glorified in Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says\u2014your Redeemer
        and Creator:\u201CI am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, who made all things.I
        alone stretched out the heavens.Who was with mewhen I made the earth?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I expose the false prophets as liarsand make fools of fortune-tellers.I
        cause the wise to give bad advice,thus proving them to be fools.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But I carry out the predictions of my prophets!By them I say to Jerusalem,
        \u2018People will live here again,\u2019and to the towns of Judah, \u2018You
        will be rebuilt;I will restore all your ruins!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When I speak to the rivers and say, \u2018Dry up!\u2019they will
        be dry.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Cyrus, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Chosen One"
      content: '  This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says to Cyrus, his
        anointed one,whose right hand he will empower.Before him, mighty kings will
        be paralyzed with fear.Their fortress gates will be opened,never to shut
        again.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CI will go
        before you, Cyrus,and level the mountains.[[COMMENT(0)]]I will smash down
        gates of bronzeand cut through bars of iron.  "
      comments:
      - number: '45:2 '
        content: As in Dead Sea Scrolls and Greek version; Masoretic Text reads <b>the
          swellings.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "And I will give you treasures hidden in the darkness\u2014secret
        riches.I will do this so you may know that I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,the
        God of Israel, the one who calls you by name.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAnd why have I called you for this work?Why did I call you
        by name when you did not know me?It is for the sake of Jacob my servant,Israel
        my chosen one.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;there is no other God.I have
        equipped you for battle,though you don\u2019t even know me,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'so all the world from east to westwill know there is no other God.I
        am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and there is no other.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I create the light and make the darkness.I send good times and bad
        times.I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, am the one who does these things.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201COpen up, O heavens,and pour out your righteousness.Let the
        earth open wideso salvation and righteousness can sprout up together.I, the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, created them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhat sorrow awaits those who argue with their Creator.Does
        a clay pot argue with its maker?Does the clay dispute with the one who shapes
        it, saying,\u2018Stop, you\u2019re doing it wrong!\u2019Does the pot exclaim,\u2018How
        clumsy can you be?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "How terrible it would be if a newborn baby said to its father,\u2018Why
        was I born?\u2019or if it said to its mother,\u2018Why did you make me this
        way?\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says\u2014the Holy One
        of Israel and your Creator:\u201CDo you question what I do for my children?Do
        you give me orders about the work of my hands?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am the one who made the earthand created people to live on it.With
        my hands I stretched out the heavens.All the stars are at my command.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Future Conversion of Gentiles
      content: "I will raise up Cyrus to fulfill my righteous purpose,and I will
        guide his actions.He will restore my city and free my captive people\u2014without
        seeking a reward!I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s Armies,
        have spoken!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CYou will
        rule the Egyptians,the Ethiopians,[[COMMENT(0)]] and the Sabeans.They will
        come to you with all their merchandise,and it will all be yours.They will
        follow you as prisoners in chains.They will fall to their knees in front
        of you and say,\u2018God is with you, and he is the only God.There is no
        other.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '45:14 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Cushites.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Truly, O God of Israel, our Savior,you work in mysterious ways.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'All craftsmen who make idols will be humiliated.They will all be
        disgraced together.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will save the people of Israelwith
        eternal salvation.Throughout everlasting ages,they will never again be humiliated
        and disgraced.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is God,and he created the heavens
        and earthand put everything in place.He made the world to be lived in,not
        to be a place of empty chaos.\u201CI am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u201D
        he says,\u201Cand there is no other.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I publicly proclaim bold promises.I do not whisper obscurities in
        some dark corner.I would not have told the people of Israel[[COMMENT(0)]]
        to seek meif I could not be found.I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, speak
        only what is trueand declare only what is right.  '
      comments:
      - number: '45:19 '
        content: Hebrew <b>of Jacob. </b>See note on 14:1.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGather together and come,you fugitives from surrounding nations.What
        fools they are who carry around their wooden idolsand pray to gods that cannot
        save!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Consult together, argue your case.Get together and decide what to
        say.Who made these things known so long ago?What idol ever told you they
        would happen?Was it not I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?For there is no
        other God but me,a righteous God and Savior.There is none but me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let all the world look to me for salvation!For I am God; there is
        no other.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I have sworn by my own name;I have spoken the truth,and I will never
        go back on my word:Every knee will bend to me,and every tongue will declare
        allegiance to me.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '45:23 '
        content: Hebrew <b>will confess; </b>Greek version reads <b>will declare
          allegiance to God. </b>Compare Rom 14:11.
    - title: 
      content: "The people will declare,\u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is
        the source of all my righteousness and strength.\u201DAnd all who were angry
        with himwill come to him and be ashamed.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Babylon\u2019s False Gods"
      content: '  Bel and Nebo, the gods of Babylon,bow as they are lowered to the
        ground.They are being hauled away on ox carts.The poor beasts stagger under
        the weight.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Both the idols and their owners are bowed down.The gods cannot protect
        the people,and the people cannot protect the gods.They go off into captivity
        together.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CListen to me, descendants of Jacob,all you who remain in Israel.I
        have cared for you since you were born.Yes, I carried you before you were
        born.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will be your God throughout your lifetime\u2014until your hair
        is white with age.I made you, and I will care for you.I will carry you along
        and save you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTo whom will you compare me?Who is my equal?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Some people pour out their silver and goldand hire a craftsman to
        make a god from it.Then they bow down and worship it!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They carry it around on their shoulders,and when they set it down,
        it stays there.It can\u2019t even move!And when someone prays to it, there
        is no answer.It can\u2019t rescue anyone from trouble.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CDo not forget this! Keep it in mind!Remember this, you guilty
        ones.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Remember the things I have done in the past.For I alone am God!I
        am God, and there is none like me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Only I can tell you the futurebefore it even happens.Everything I
        plan will come to pass,for I do whatever I wish.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will call a swift bird of prey from the east\u2014a leader from
        a distant land to come and do my bidding.I have said what I would do,and
        I will do it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CListen to me, you stubborn peoplewho are so far from doing
        right.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Prediction of Babylon\u2019s Fall"
      content: "  \u201CCome down, virgin daughter of Babylon, and sit in the dust.For
        your days of sitting on a throne have ended.O daughter of Babylonia,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        never again will you bethe lovely princess, tender and delicate.  "
      comments:
      - number: '47:1 '
        content: Or <b>Chaldea; </b>also in 47:5.
    - title: 
      content: 'Take heavy millstones and grind flour.Remove your veil, and strip
        off your robe.Expose yourself to public view.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '47:2 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Bare your legs; pass through the rivers.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "You will be naked and burdened with shame.I will take vengeance against
        you without pity.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Our Redeemer, whose name is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies,is the Holy One of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CO beautiful Babylon, sit now in darkness and silence.Never
        again will you be known as the queen of kingdoms.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For I was angry with my chosen peopleand punished them by letting
        them fall into your hands.But you, Babylon, showed them no mercy.You oppressed
        even the elderly.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You said, \u2018I will reign forever as queen of the world!\u2019You
        did not reflect on your actionsor think about their consequences.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CListen to this, you pleasure-loving kingdom,living at ease
        and feeling secure.You say, \u2018I am the only one, and there is no other.I
        will never be a widow or lose my children.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Well, both these things will come upon you in a moment:widowhood
        and the loss of your children.Yes, these calamities will come upon you,despite
        all your witchcraft and magic.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou felt secure in your wickedness.\u2018No one sees me,\u2019
        you said.But your \u2018wisdom\u2019 and \u2018knowledge\u2019 have led you
        astray,and you said, \u2018I am the only one, and there is no other.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So disaster will overtake you,and you won\u2019t be able to charm
        it away.Calamity will fall upon you,and you won\u2019t be able to buy your
        way out.A catastrophe will strike you suddenly,one for which you are not
        prepared.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNow use your magical charms!Use the spells you have worked
        at all these years!Maybe they will do you some good.Maybe they can make someone
        afraid of you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'All the advice you receive has made you tired.Where are all your
        astrologers,those stargazers who make predictions each month?Let them stand
        up and save you from what the future holds.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But they are like straw burning in a fire;they cannot save themselves
        from the flame.You will get no help from them at all;their hearth is no place
        to sit for warmth.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "God\u2019s Stubborn People"
      content: "  \u201CListen to me, O family of Jacob,you who are called by the
        name of Israeland born into the family of Judah.Listen, you who take oaths
        in the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>and call on the God of Israel.You
        don\u2019t keep your promises,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "even though you call yourself the holy cityand talk about depending
        on the God of Israel,whose name is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of Heaven\u2019s
        Armies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Long ago I told you what was going to happen.Then suddenly I took
        action,and all my predictions came true.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For I know how stubborn and obstinate you are.Your necks are as unbending
        as iron.Your heads are as hard as bronze.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "That is why I told you what would happen;I told you beforehand what
        I was going to do.Then you could never say, \u2018My idols did it.My wooden
        image and metal god commanded it to happen!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have heard my predictions and seen them fulfilled,but you refuse
        to admit it.Now I will tell you new things,secrets you have not yet heard.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They are brand new, not things from the past.So you cannot say, \u2018We
        knew that all the time!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYes, I will tell you of things that are entirely new,things
        you never heard of before.For I know so well what traitors you are.You have
        been rebels from birth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yet for my own sake and for the honor of my name,I will hold back
        my anger and not wipe you out.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I have refined you, but not as silver is refined.Rather, I have refined
        you in the furnace of suffering.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Freedom from Babylon
      content: "I will rescue you for my sake\u2014yes, for my own sake!I will not
        let my reputation be tarnished,and I will not share my glory with idols!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CListen to me, O family of Jacob,Israel my chosen one!I alone
        am God,the First and the Last.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It was my hand that laid the foundations of the earth,my right hand
        that spread out the heavens above.When I call out the stars,they all appear
        in order.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Have any of your idols ever told you this?Come, all of you, and listen:The
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has chosen Cyrus as his ally.He will use him
        to put an end to the empire of Babylonand to destroy the Babylonian[[COMMENT(0)]]
        armies.  '
      comments:
      - number: '48:14 '
        content: Or <b>Chaldean.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI have said it: I am calling Cyrus!I will send him on this
        errand and will help him succeed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Come closer, and listen to this.From the beginning I have told you
        plainly what would happen.\u201DAnd now the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and his Spirithave sent me with this message.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says\u2014your Redeemer,
        the Holy One of Israel:\u201CI am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God,who
        teaches you what is good for youand leads you along the paths you should
        follow.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Oh, that you had listened to my commands!Then you would have had
        peace flowing like a gentle riverand righteousness rolling over you like
        waves in the sea.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Your descendants would have been like the sands along the seashore\u2014too
        many to count!There would have been no need for your destruction,or for cutting
        off your family name.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yet even now, be free from your captivity!Leave Babylon and the Babylonians.[[COMMENT(0)]]Sing
        out this message!Shout it to the ends of the earth!The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has redeemed his servants,the people of Israel.[[COMMENT(1)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '48:20a '
        content: Or <b>the Chaldeans.</b>
      - number: '48:20b '
        content: Hebrew <b>his servant, Jacob. </b>See note on 14:1.
    - title: 
      content: 'They were not thirstywhen he led them through the desert.He divided
        the rock,and water gushed out for them to drink.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Servant Commissioned"
      content: '  Listen to me, all you in distant lands!Pay attention, you who are
        far away!The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> called me before my birth;from within
        the womb he called me by name.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He made my words of judgment as sharp as a sword.He has hidden me
        in the shadow of his hand.I am like a sharp arrow in his quiver.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He said to me, \u201CYou are my servant, Israel,and you will bring
        me glory.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I replied, \u201CBut my work seems so useless!I have spent my strength
        for nothing and to no purpose.Yet I leave it all in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        hand;I will trust God for my reward.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And now the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> speaks\u2014the one who formed
        me in my mother\u2019s womb to be his servant,who commissioned me to bring
        Israel back to him.The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has honored me,and my
        God has given me strength.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He says, \u201CYou will do more than restore the people of Israel
        to me.I will make you a light to the Gentiles,and you will bring my salvation
        to the ends of the earth.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: "Promises of Israel\u2019s Restoration"
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the Redeemerand Holy One of Israel,says
        to the one who is despised and rejected by the nations,to the one who is
        the servant of rulers:\u201CKings will stand at attention when you pass by.Princes
        will also bow lowbecause of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the faithful
        one,the Holy One of Israel, who has chosen you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CAt just the
        right time, I will respond to you.[[COMMENT(0)]]On the day of salvation I
        will help you.I will protect you and give you to the peopleas my covenant
        with them.Through you I will reestablish the land of Israeland assign it
        to its own people again.  "
      comments:
      - number: '49:8 '
        content: Greek version reads <b>I heard you. </b>Compare 2 Cor 6:2.
    - title: 
      content: "I will say to the prisoners, \u2018Come out in freedom,\u2019and
        to those in darkness, \u2018Come into the light.\u2019They will be my sheep,
        grazing in green pasturesand on hills that were previously bare.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will neither hunger nor thirst.The searing sun will not reach
        them anymore.For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> in his mercy will lead them;he
        will lead them beside cool waters.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And I will make my mountains into level paths for them.The highways
        will be raised above the valleys.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "See, my people will return from far away,from lands to the north
        and west,and from as far south as Egypt.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '49:12 '
        content: As in Dead Sea Scrolls, which read <b>from the region of Aswan,
          </b>which is in southern Egypt. Masoretic Text reads <b>from the region
          of Sinim.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Sing for joy, O heavens!Rejoice, O earth!Burst into song, O mountains!For
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has comforted his peopleand will have compassion
        on them in their suffering.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yet Jerusalem[[COMMENT(0)]] says, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has deserted us;the Lord has forgotten us.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '49:14 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Zion.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNever! Can a mother forget her nursing child?Can she feel no
        love for the child she has borne?But even if that were possible,I would not
        forget you!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "See, I have written your name on the palms of my hands.Always in
        my mind is a picture of Jerusalem\u2019s walls in ruins.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Soon your descendants will come back,and all who are trying to destroy
        you will go away.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Look around you and see,for all your children will come back to you.As
        surely as I live,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,\u201Cthey will
        be like jewels or bridal ornaments for you to display.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CEven the most desolate parts of your abandoned landwill soon
        be crowded with your people.Your enemies who enslaved youwill be far away.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The generations born in exile will return and say,\u2018We need more
        room! It\u2019s crowded here!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then you will think to yourself,\u2018Who has given me all these
        descendants?For most of my children were killed,and the rest were carried
        away into exile.I was left here all alone.Where did all these people come
        from?Who bore these children?Who raised them for me?\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CSee,
        I will give a signal to the godless nations.They will carry your little sons
        back to you in their arms;they will bring your daughters on their shoulders.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Kings and queens will serve youand care for all your needs.They will
        bow to the earth before youand lick the dust from your feet.Then you will
        know that I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.Those who trust in me will
        never be put to shame.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Who can snatch the plunder of war from the hands of a warrior?Who
        can demand that a tyrant[[COMMENT(0)]] let his captives go?  '
      comments:
      - number: '49:24 '
        content: As in Dead Sea Scrolls, Syriac version, and Latin Vulgate (also
          see 49:25); Masoretic Text reads <b>a righteous person.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says,\u201CThe captives of warriors
        will be released,and the plunder of tyrants will be retrieved.For I will
        fight those who fight you,and I will save your children.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "  This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CWas your
        mother sent away because I divorced her?Did I sell you as slaves to my creditors?No,
        you were sold because of your sins.And your mother, too, was taken because
        of your sins.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Why was no one there when I came?Why didn\u2019t anyone answer when
        I called?Is it because I have no power to rescue?No, that is not the reason!For
        I can speak to the sea and make it dry up!I can turn rivers into deserts
        covered with dying fish.  "
      comments: []
    - title: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Obedient Servant"
      content: "I dress the skies in darkness,covering them with clothes of mourning.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has given me his words
        of wisdom,so that I know how to comfort the weary.Morning by morning he wakens
        meand opens my understanding to his will.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has spoken to me,and I
        have listened.I have not rebelled or turned away.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I offered my back to those who beat meand my cheeks to those who
        pulled out my beard.I did not hide my facefrom mockery and spitting.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Because the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> helps me,I will
        not be disgraced.Therefore, I have set my face like a stone,determined to
        do his will.And I know that I will not be put to shame.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He who gives me justice is near.Who will dare to bring charges against
        me now?Where are my accusers?Let them appear!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'See, the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is on my side!Who
        will declare me guilty?All my enemies will be destroyedlike old clothes that
        have been eaten by moths!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Who among you fears the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>and obeys his
        servant?If you are walking in darkness,without a ray of light,trust in the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>and rely on your God.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Call to Trust the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
      content: "  \u201CListen to me, all who hope for deliverance\u2014all who seek
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!Consider the rock from which you were cut,the
        quarry from which you were mined.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yes, think about Abraham, your ancestor,and Sarah, who gave birth
        to your nation.Abraham was only one man when I called him.But when I blessed
        him, he became a great nation.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will comfort Israel[[COMMENT(0)]]
        againand have pity on her ruins.Her desert will blossom like Eden,her barren
        wilderness like the garden of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.Joy and gladness
        will be found there.Songs of thanksgiving will fill the air.  '
      comments:
      - number: '51:3 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Zion; </b>also in 51:16.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CListen to me, my people.Hear me, Israel,for my law will be
        proclaimed,and my justice will become a light to the nations.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My mercy and justice are coming soon.My salvation is on the way.My
        strong arm will bring justice to the nations.All distant lands will look
        to meand wait in hope for my powerful arm.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Look up to the skies above,and gaze down on the earth below.For the
        skies will disappear like smoke,and the earth will wear out like a piece
        of clothing.The people of the earth will die like flies,but my salvation
        lasts forever.My righteous rule will never end!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CListen to me, you who know right from wrong,you who cherish
        my law in your hearts.Do not be afraid of people\u2019s scorn,nor fear their
        insults.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the moth will devour them as it devours clothing.The worm will
        eat at them as it eats wool.But my righteousness will last forever.My salvation
        will continue from generation to generation.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Wake up, wake up, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>! Clothe yourself
        with strength!Flex your mighty right arm!Rouse yourself as in the days of
        oldwhen you slew Egypt, the dragon of the Nile.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '51:9 '
        content: Hebrew <b>You slew Rahab; you pierced the dragon. </b>Rahab is the
          name of a mythical sea monster that represents chaos in ancient literature.
          The name is used here as a poetic name for Egypt.
    - title: 
      content: 'Are you not the same today,the one who dried up the sea,making a
        path of escape through the depthsso that your people could cross over?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Those who have been ransomed by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will
        return.They will enter Jerusalem[[COMMENT(0)]] singing,crowned with everlasting
        joy.Sorrow and mourning will disappear,and they will be filled with joy and
        gladness.  '
      comments:
      - number: '51:11 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Zion.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI, yes I, am the one who comforts you.So why are you afraid
        of mere humans,who wither like the grass and disappear?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yet you have forgotten the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, your Creator,the
        one who stretched out the sky like a canopyand laid the foundations of the
        earth.Will you remain in constant dread of human oppressors?Will you continue
        to fear the anger of your enemies?Where is their fury and anger now?It is
        gone!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Soon all you captives will be released!Imprisonment, starvation,
        and death will not be your fate!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God,who stirs up the
        sea, causing its waves to roar.My name is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And I have put my words in your mouthand hidden you safely in my
        hand.I stretched out[[COMMENT(0)]] the sky like a canopyand laid the foundations
        of the earth.I am the one who says to Israel,\u2018You are my people!\u2019\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '51:16 '
        content: As in Syriac version (see also 51:13); Hebrew reads <b>planted.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Wake up, wake up, O Jerusalem!You have drunk the cup of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        fury.You have drunk the cup of terror,tipping out its last drops.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Not one of your children is left aliveto take your hand and guide
        you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'These two calamities have fallen on you:desolation and destruction,
        famine and war.And who is left to sympathize with you?Who is left to comfort
        you?[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '51:19 '
        content: As in Dead Sea Scrolls and Greek, Latin, and Syriac versions; Masoretic
          Text reads <b>How can I comfort you?</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'For your children have fainted and lie in the streets,helpless as
        antelopes caught in a net.The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has poured out
        his fury;God has rebuked them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But now listen to this, you afflicted oneswho sit in a drunken stupor,though
        not from drinking wine.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,your God and
        Defender, says:\u201CSee, I have taken the terrible cup from your hands.You
        will drink no more of my fury.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Deliverance for Jerusalem
      content: '  Wake up, wake up, O Zion!Clothe yourself with strength.Put on your
        beautiful clothes, O holy city of Jerusalem,for unclean and godless people
        will enter your gates no longer.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Rise from the dust, O Jerusalem.Sit in a place of honor.Remove the
        chains of slavery from your neck,O captive daughter of Zion.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CWhen
        I sold you into exile,I received no payment.Now I can redeem youwithout having
        to pay for you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says: \u201CLong
        ago my people chose to live in Egypt. Now they are oppressed by Assyria. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "What is this?\u201D asks the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. \u201CWhy
        are my people enslaved again? Those who rule them shout in exultation.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        My name is blasphemed all day long.[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '52:5a '
        content: As in Dead Sea Scrolls; Masoretic Text reads <b>Those who rule them
          wail.</b>
      - number: '52:5b '
        content: Greek version reads <b>The Gentiles continually blaspheme my name
          because of you. </b>Compare Rom 2:24.
    - title: 
      content: "But I will reveal my name to my people, and they will come to know
        its power. Then at last they will recognize that I am the one who speaks
        to them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'How beautiful on the mountainsare the feet of the messenger who brings
        good news,the good news of peace and salvation,the news that the God of Israel[[COMMENT(0)]]
        reigns!  '
      comments:
      - number: '52:7 '
        content: Hebrew <b>of Zion.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'The watchmen shout and sing with joy,for before their very eyesthey
        see the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> returning to Jerusalem.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '52:8 '
        content: Hebrew <b>to Zion.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Let the ruins of Jerusalem break into joyful song,for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has comforted his people.He has redeemed Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has demonstrated his holy powerbefore
        the eyes of all the nations.All the ends of the earth will seethe victory
        of our God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Get out! Get out and leave your captivity,where everything you touch
        is unclean.Get out of there and purify yourselves,you who carry home the
        sacred objects of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - title: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Suffering Servant"
      content: 'You will not leave in a hurry,running for your lives.For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will go ahead of you;yes, the God of Israel will protect you from behind.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'See, my servant will prosper;he will be highly exalted.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But many were amazed when they saw him.[[COMMENT(0)]]His face was
        so disfigured he seemed hardly human,and from his appearance, one would scarcely
        know he was a man.  '
      comments:
      - number: '52:14 '
        content: As in Syriac version; Hebrew reads <b>you.</b>
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  Who has believed our message?To whom has the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        revealed his powerful arm?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My servant grew up in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s presence
        like a tender green shoot,like a root in dry ground.There was nothing beautiful
        or majestic about his appearance,nothing to attract us to him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He was despised and rejected\u2014a man of sorrows, acquainted with
        deepest grief.We turned our backs on him and looked the other way.He was
        despised, and we did not care.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yet it was our weaknesses he carried;it was our sorrows[[COMMENT(0)]]
        that weighed him down.And we thought his troubles were a punishment from
        God,a punishment for his own sins!  '
      comments:
      - number: '53:4 '
        content: Or <b>Yet it was our sicknesses he carried; / it was our diseases.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'But he was pierced for our rebellion,crushed for our sins.He was
        beaten so we could be whole.He was whipped so we could be healed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All of us, like sheep, have strayed away.We have left God\u2019s
        paths to follow our own.Yet the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> laid on himthe
        sins of us all.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He was oppressed and treated harshly,yet he never said a word.He
        was led like a lamb to the slaughter.And as a sheep is silent before the
        shearers,he did not open his mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Unjustly condemned,he was led away.[[COMMENT(0)]]No one cared that
        he died without descendants,that his life was cut short in midstream.[[COMMENT(1)]]But
        he was struck downfor the rebellion of my people.  '
      comments:
      - number: '53:8a '
        content: Greek version reads <b>He was humiliated and received no justice.
          </b>Compare Acts 8:33.
      - number: '53:8b '
        content: Or <b>As for his contemporaries, / who cared that his life was cut
          short in midstream? </b>Greek version reads <b>Who can speak of his descendants?
          / For his life was taken from the earth. </b>Compare Acts 8:33.
    - title: 
      content: "He had done no wrongand had never deceived anyone.But he was buried
        like a criminal;he was put in a rich man\u2019s grave.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But it was the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s good plan to crush
        himand cause him grief.Yet when his life is made an offering for sin,he will
        have many descendants.He will enjoy a long life,and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        good plan will prosper in his hands.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When he sees all that is accomplished by his anguish,he will be satisfied.And
        because of his experience,my righteous servant will make it possiblefor many
        to be counted righteous,for he will bear all their sins.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Future Glory for Jerusalem
      content: "  \u201CSing, O childless woman,you who have never given birth!Break
        into loud and joyful song, O Jerusalem,you who have never been in labor.For
        the desolate woman now has more childrenthan the woman who lives with her
        husband,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CEnlarge your house; build an addition.Spread out your home,
        and spare no expense!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For you will soon be bursting at the seams.Your descendants will
        occupy other nationsand resettle the ruined cities.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CFear not; you will no longer live in shame.Don\u2019t be afraid;
        there is no more disgrace for you.You will no longer remember the shame of
        your youthand the sorrows of widowhood.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For your Creator will be your husband;the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        of Heaven\u2019s Armies is his name!He is your Redeemer, the Holy One of
        Israel,the God of all the earth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has called you back from your
        grief\u2014as though you were a young wife abandoned by her husband,\u201Dsays
        your God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CFor a brief moment I abandoned you,but with great compassion
        I will take you back.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In a burst of anger I turned my face away for a little while.But
        with everlasting love I will have compassion on you,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        your Redeemer.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CJust as I swore in the time of Noahthat I would never again
        let a flood cover the earth,so now I swearthat I will never again be angry
        and punish you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the mountains may moveand the hills disappear,but even then my
        faithful love for you will remain.My covenant of blessing will never be broken,\u201Dsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, who has mercy on you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CO storm-battered city,troubled and desolate!I will rebuild
        you with precious jewelsand make your foundations from lapis lazuli.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will make your towers of sparkling rubies,your gates of shining
        gems,and your walls of precious stones.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will teach all your children,and they will enjoy great peace.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will be secure under a government that is just and fair.Your
        enemies will stay far away.You will live in peace,and terror will not come
        near.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If any nation comes to fight you,it is not because I sent them.Whoever
        attacks you will go down in defeat.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI have created the blacksmithwho fans the coals beneath the
        forgeand makes the weapons of destruction.And I have created the armies that
        destroy.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Invitation to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Salvation"
      content: "  \u201CIs anyone thirsty?Come and drink\u2014even if you have no
        money!Come, take your choice of wine or milk\u2014it\u2019s all free!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Why spend your money on food that does not give you strength?Why
        pay for food that does you no good?Listen to me, and you will eat what is
        good.You will enjoy the finest food.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CCome to me with your ears wide open.Listen, and you will find
        life.I will make an everlasting covenant with you.I will give you all the
        unfailing love I promised to David.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'See how I used him to display my power among the peoples.I made him
        a leader among the nations.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You also will command nations you do not know,and peoples unknown
        to you will come running to obey,because I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God,the Holy One of Israel, have made you glorious.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Seek the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> while you can find him.Call
        on him now while he is near.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let the wicked change their waysand banish the very thought of doing
        wrong.Let them turn to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> that he may have mercy
        on them.Yes, turn to our God, for he will forgive generously.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CMy thoughts are nothing like your thoughts,\u201D says the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CAnd my ways are far beyond anything you
        could imagine.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For just as the heavens are higher than the earth,so my ways are
        higher than your waysand my thoughts higher than your thoughts.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe rain and snow come down from the heavensand stay on the
        ground to water the earth.They cause the grain to grow,producing seed for
        the farmerand bread for the hungry.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It is the same with my word.I send it out, and it always produces
        fruit.It will accomplish all I want it to,and it will prosper everywhere
        I send it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will live in joy and peace.The mountains and hills will burst
        into song,and the trees of the field will clap their hands!  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Blessings for All Nations
      content: "  This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CBe just
        and fair to all.Do what is right and good,for I am coming soon to rescue
        youand to display my righteousness among you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Blessed are all thosewho are careful to do this.Blessed are those
        who honor my Sabbath days of restand keep themselves from doing wrong.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CDon\u2019t let foreigners who commit themselves to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        say,\u2018The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will never let me be part of his
        people.\u2019And don\u2019t let the eunuchs say,\u2018I\u2019m a dried-up
        tree with no children and no future.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For this is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:I will bless
        those eunuchswho keep my Sabbath days holyand who choose to do what pleases
        meand commit their lives to me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will give them\u2014within the walls of my house\u2014a memorial
        and a namefar greater than sons and daughters could give.For the name I give
        them is an everlasting one.It will never disappear!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI will also bless the foreigners who commit themselves to the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,who serve him and love his name,who worship him
        and do not desecrate the Sabbath day of rest,and who hold fast to my covenant.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will bring them to my holy mountain of Jerusalemand will fill them
        with joy in my house of prayer.I will accept their burnt offerings and sacrifices,because
        my Temple will be called a house of prayer for all nations.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Sinful Leaders Condemned
      content: "For the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,who brings back the
        outcasts of Israel, says:I will bring others, too,besides my people Israel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Come, wild animals of the field!Come, wild animals of the forest!Come
        and devour my people!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the leaders of my people\u2014the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        watchmen, his shepherds\u2014are blind and ignorant.They are like silent
        watchdogsthat give no warning when danger comes.They love to lie around,
        sleeping and dreaming.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Like greedy dogs, they are never satisfied.They are ignorant shepherds,all
        following their own pathand intent on personal gain.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  Good people pass away;the godly often die before their time.But
        no one seems to care or wonder why.No one seems to understandthat God is
        protecting them from the evil to come.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Idolatrous Worship Condemned
      content: 'For those who follow godly pathswill rest in peace when they die.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut you\u2014come here, you witches\u2019 children,you offspring
        of adulterers and prostitutes!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Whom do you mock,making faces and sticking out your tongues?You children
        of sinners and liars!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You worship your idols with great passionbeneath the oaks and under
        every green tree.You sacrifice your children down in the valleys,among the
        jagged rocks in the cliffs.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your gods are the smooth stones in the valleys.You worship them with
        liquid offerings and grain offerings.They, not I, are your inheritance.Do
        you think all this makes me happy?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have committed adultery on every high mountain.There you have
        worshiped idolsand have been unfaithful to me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have put pagan symbolson your doorposts and behind your doors.You
        have left meand climbed into bed with these detestable gods.You have committed
        yourselves to them.You love to look at their naked bodies.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You have gone to Molech[[COMMENT(0)]]with olive oil and many perfumes,sending
        your agents far and wide,even to the world of the dead.[[COMMENT(1)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '57:9a '
        content: Or <b>to the king.</b>
      - number: '57:9b '
        content: Hebrew <b>to Sheol.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'You grew weary in your search,but you never gave up.Desire gave you
        renewed strength,and you did not grow weary.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAre you afraid of these idols?Do they terrify you?Is that why
        you have lied to meand forgotten me and my words?Is it because of my long
        silencethat you no longer fear me?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Now I will expose your so-called good deeds.None of them will help
        you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: God Forgives the Repentant
      content: "Let\u2019s see if your idols can save youwhen you cry to them for
        help.Why, a puff of wind can knock them down!If you just breathe on them,
        they fall over!But whoever trusts in me will inherit the landand possess
        my holy mountain.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "God says, \u201CRebuild the road!Clear away the rocks and stonesso
        my people can return from captivity.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The high and lofty one who lives in eternity,the Holy One, says this:\u201CI
        live in the high and holy placewith those whose spirits are contrite and
        humble.I restore the crushed spirit of the humbleand revive the courage of
        those with repentant hearts.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I will not fight against you forever;I will not always be angry.If
        I were, all people would pass away\u2014all the souls I have made.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I was angry,so I punished these greedy people.I withdrew from them,but
        they kept going on their own stubborn way.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I have seen what they do,but I will heal them anyway!I will lead
        them.I will comfort those who mourn,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "bringing words of praise to their lips.May they have abundant peace,
        both near and far,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, who heals them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut those who still reject me are like the restless sea,which
        is never stillbut continually churns up mud and dirt.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: True and False Worship
      content: "  \u201CShout with the voice of a trumpet blast.Shout aloud! Don\u2019t
        be timid.Tell my people Israel[[COMMENT(0)]] of their sins!  "
      comments:
      - number: '58:1 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Jacob. </b>See note on 14:1.
    - title: 
      content: 'Yet they act so pious!They come to the Temple every dayand seem delighted
        to learn all about me.They act like a righteous nationthat would never abandon
        the laws of its God.They ask me to take action on their behalf,pretending
        they want to be near me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018We have fasted before you!\u2019 they say.\u2018Why aren\u2019t
        you impressed?We have been very hard on ourselves,and you don\u2019t even
        notice it!\u2019\u201CI will tell you why!\u201D I respond.\u201CIt\u2019s
        because you are fasting to please yourselves.Even while you fast,you keep
        oppressing your workers.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'What good is fastingwhen you keep on fighting and quarreling?This
        kind of fastingwill never get you anywhere with me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You humble yourselvesby going through the motions of penance,bowing
        your headslike reeds bending in the wind.You dress in burlapand cover yourselves
        with ashes.Is this what you call fasting?Do you really think this will please
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNo, this is the kind of fasting I want:Free those who are wrongly
        imprisoned;lighten the burden of those who work for you.Let the oppressed
        go free,and remove the chains that bind people.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Share your food with the hungry,and give shelter to the homeless.Give
        clothes to those who need them,and do not hide from relatives who need your
        help.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen your salvation will come like the dawn,and your wounds
        will quickly heal.Your godliness will lead you forward,and the glory of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will protect you from behind.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then when you call, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will answer.\u2018Yes,
        I am here,\u2019 he will quickly reply.\u201CRemove the heavy yoke of oppression.Stop
        pointing your finger and spreading vicious rumors!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Feed the hungry,and help those in trouble.Then your light will shine
        out from the darkness,and the darkness around you will be as bright as noon.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will guide you continually,giving
        you water when you are dryand restoring your strength.You will be like a
        well-watered garden,like an ever-flowing spring.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Some of you will rebuild the deserted ruins of your cities.Then you
        will be known as a rebuilder of wallsand a restorer of homes.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CKeep the Sabbath day holy.Don\u2019t pursue your own interests
        on that day,but enjoy the Sabbathand speak of it with delight as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        holy day.Honor the Sabbath in everything you do on that day,and don\u2019t
        follow your own desires or talk idly.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Warnings against Sin
      content: "  Listen! The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s arm is not too weak
        to save you,nor is his ear too deaf to hear you call.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It\u2019s your sins that have cut you off from God.Because of your
        sins, he has turned awayand will not listen anymore.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your hands are the hands of murderers,and your fingers are filthy
        with sin.Your lips are full of lies,and your mouth spews corruption.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "No one cares about being fair and honest.The people\u2019s lawsuits
        are based on lies.They conceive evil deedsand then give birth to sin.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They hatch deadly snakesand weave spiders\u2019 webs.Whoever eats
        their eggs will die;whoever cracks them will hatch a viper.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their webs can\u2019t be made into clothing,and nothing they do is
        productive.All their activity is filled with sin,and violence is their trademark.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Their feet run to do evil,and they rush to commit murder.They think
        only about sinning.Misery and destruction always follow them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They don\u2019t know where to find peaceor what it means to be just
        and good.They have mapped out crooked roads,and no one who follows them knows
        a moment\u2019s peace.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So there is no justice among us,and we know nothing about right living.We
        look for light but find only darkness.We look for bright skies but walk in
        gloom.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We grope like the blind along a wall,feeling our way like people
        without eyes.Even at brightest noontime,we stumble as though it were dark.Among
        the living,we are like the dead.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We growl like hungry bears;we moan like mournful doves.We look for
        justice, but it never comes.We look for rescue, but it is far away from us.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For our sins are piled up before Godand testify against us.Yes, we
        know what sinners we are.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We know we have rebelled and have denied the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.We
        have turned our backs on our God.We know how unfair and oppressive we have
        been,carefully planning our deceitful lies.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Our courts oppose the righteous,and justice is nowhere to be found.Truth
        stumbles in the streets,and honesty has been outlawed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, truth is gone,and anyone who renounces evil is attacked.The
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> looked and was displeasedto find there was no
        justice.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He was amazed to see that no one intervenedto help the oppressed.So
        he himself stepped in to save them with his strong arm,and his justice sustained
        him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He put on righteousness as his body armorand placed the helmet of
        salvation on his head.He clothed himself with a robe of vengeanceand wrapped
        himself in a cloak of divine passion.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will repay his enemies for their evil deeds.His fury will fall
        on his foes.He will pay them back even to the ends of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: In the west, people will respect the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;in
        the east, they will glorify him.For he will come like a raging flood tidedriven
        by the breath of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps> 
        </smallcaps>
      comments:
      - number: '59:19 '
        content: Or <b>When the enemy comes like a raging flood tide, / the Spirit
          of the <span class="ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf">Lord</span> will drive him
          back.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe Redeemer will come to Jerusalemto buy back those in Israelwho
        have turned from their sins,\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments:
      - number: '59:20 '
        content: Hebrew <b>The Redeemer will come to Zion / to buy back those in
          Jacob / who have turned from their sins. </b>Greek version reads <b>The
          one who rescues will come on behalf of Zion, / and he will turn Jacob away
          from ungodliness. </b>Compare Rom 11:26.
  - verses:
    - title: Future Glory for Jerusalem
      content: "  \u201CArise, Jerusalem! Let your light shine for all to see.For
        the glory of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> rises to shine on you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Darkness as black as night covers all the nations of the earth,but
        the glory of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> rises and appears over you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'All nations will come to your light;mighty kings will come to see
        your radiance.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CLook and see, for everyone is coming home!Your sons are coming
        from distant lands;your little daughters will be carried home.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your eyes will shine,and your heart will thrill with joy,for merchants
        from around the world will come to you.They will bring you the wealth of
        many lands.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Vast caravans of camels will converge on you,the camels of Midian
        and Ephah.The people of Sheba will bring gold and frankincenseand will come
        worshiping the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The flocks of Kedar will be given to you,and the rams of Nebaioth
        will be brought for my altars.I will accept their offerings,and I will make
        my Temple glorious.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAnd what do I see flying like clouds to Israel,like doves to
        their nests?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They are ships from the ends of the earth,from lands that trust in
        me,led by the great ships of Tarshish.They are bringing the people of Israel
        home from far away,carrying their silver and gold.They will honor the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God,the Holy One of Israel,for he has filled you with splendor.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CForeigners will come to rebuild your towns,and their kings
        will serve you.For though I have destroyed you in my anger,I will now have
        mercy on you through my grace.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your gates will stay open day and nightto receive the wealth of many
        lands.The kings of the world will be led as captivesin a victory procession.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the nations that refuse to serve youwill be destroyed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe glory of Lebanon will be yours\u2014the forests of cypress,
        fir, and pine\u2014to beautify my sanctuary.My Temple will be glorious!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The descendants of your tormentorswill come and bow before you.Those
        who despised youwill kiss your feet.They will call you the City of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and
        Zion of the Holy One of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThough you were once despised and hated,with no one traveling
        through you,I will make you beautiful forever,a joy to all generations.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Powerful kings and mighty nationswill satisfy your every need,as
        though you were a childnursing at the breast of a queen.You will know at
        last that I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,am your Savior and your Redeemer,the
        Mighty One of Israel.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '60:16 '
        content: Hebrew <b>of Jacob. </b>See note on 14:1.
    - title: 
      content: 'I will exchange your bronze for gold,your iron for silver,your wood
        for bronze,and your stones for iron.I will make peace your leaderand righteousness
        your ruler.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Violence will disappear from your land;the desolation and destruction
        of war will end.Salvation will surround you like city walls,and praise will
        be on the lips of all who enter there.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNo longer will you need the sun to shine by day,nor the moon
        to give its light by night,for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will
        be your everlasting light,and your God will be your glory.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your sun will never set;your moon will not go down.For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will be your everlasting light.Your days of mourning will come to an end.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'All your people will be righteous.They will possess their land forever,for
        I will plant them there with my own handsin order to bring myself glory.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Good News for the Oppressed
      content: '  The Spirit of the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is upon
        me,for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has anointed meto bring good news
        to the poor.He has sent me to comfort the brokenheartedand to proclaim that
        captives will be releasedand prisoners will be freed.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '61:1 '
        content: Greek version reads <b>and the blind will see. </b>Compare Luke
          4:18.
    - title: 
      content: "He has sent me to tell those who mournthat the time of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        favor has come,[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>and with it, the day of God\u2019s
        anger against their enemies.</smallcaps>  "
      comments:
      - number: '61:2 '
        content: Or <b>to proclaim the acceptable year of the <span class="ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf">Lord</span>.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'To all who mourn in Israel,[[COMMENT(0)]]he will give a crown of
        beauty for ashes,a joyous blessing instead of mourning,festive praise instead
        of despair.In their righteousness, they will be like great oaksthat the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has planted for his own glory.  '
      comments:
      - number: '61:3 '
        content: Hebrew <b>in Zion.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'They will rebuild the ancient ruins,repairing cities destroyed long
        ago.They will revive them,though they have been deserted for many generations.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Foreigners will be your servants.They will feed your flocksand plow
        your fieldsand tend your vineyards.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will be called priests of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,ministers
        of our God.You will feed on the treasures of the nationsand boast in their
        riches.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Instead of shame and dishonor,you will enjoy a double share of honor.You
        will possess a double portion of prosperity in your land,and everlasting
        joy will be yours.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CFor I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, love justice.I hate
        robbery and wrongdoing.I will faithfully reward my people for their sufferingand
        make an everlasting covenant with them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Their descendants will be recognizedand honored among the nations.Everyone
        will realize that they are a peoplethe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has blessed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am overwhelmed with joy in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> my God!For
        he has dressed me with the clothing of salvationand draped me in a robe of
        righteousness.I am like a bridegroom dressed for his weddingor a bride with
        her jewels.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Isaiah\u2019s Prayer for Jerusalem"
      content: '  Because I love Zion,I will not keep still.Because my heart yearns
        for Jerusalem,I cannot remain silent.I will not stop praying for heruntil
        her righteousness shines like the dawn,and her salvation blazes like a burning
        torch.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The nations will see your righteousness.World leaders will be blinded
        by your glory.And you will be given a new nameby the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        own mouth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will hold you in his hand for all
        to see\u2014a splendid crown in the hand of God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Never again will you be called \u201CThe Forsaken City\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]or
        \u201CThe Desolate Land.\u201D[[COMMENT(1)]]Your new name will be \u201CThe
        City of God\u2019s Delight\u201D[[COMMENT(2)]]and \u201CThe Bride of God,\u201D[[COMMENT(3)]]for
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> delights in youand will claim you as his
        bride.  "
      comments:
      - number: '62:4a '
        content: "Hebrew <b>Azubah, </b>which means \u201Cforsaken.\u201D"
      - number: '62:4b '
        content: "Hebrew <b>Shemamah, </b>which means \u201Cdesolate.\u201D"
      - number: '62:4c '
        content: "Hebrew <b>Hephzibah, </b>which means \u201Cmy delight is in her.\u201D"
      - number: '62:4d '
        content: "Hebrew <b>Beulah, </b>which means \u201Cmarried.\u201D"
    - title: 
      content: 'Your children will commit themselves to you, O Jerusalem,just as
        a young man commits himself to his bride.Then God will rejoice over youas
        a bridegroom rejoices over his bride.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'O Jerusalem, I have posted watchmen on your walls;they will pray
        day and night, continually.Take no rest, all you who pray to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Give the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> no rest until he completes his
        work,until he makes Jerusalem the pride of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has sworn to Jerusalem by his own
        strength:\u201CI will never again hand you over to your enemies.Never again
        will foreign warriors comeand take away your grain and new wine.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You raised the grain, and you will eat it,praising the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.Within
        the courtyards of the Temple,you yourselves will drink the wine you have
        pressed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Go out through the gates!Prepare the highway for my people to return!Smooth
        out the road; pull out the boulders;raise a flag for all the nations to see.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has sent this message to every land:\u201CTell
        the people of Israel,[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2018Look, your Savior is coming.See,
        he brings his reward with him as he comes.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '62:11 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Tell the daughter of Zion.</b>
  - verses:
    - title: "Judgment against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s Enemies"
      content: "  Who is this who comes from Edom,from the city of Bozrah,with his
        clothing stained red?Who is this in royal robes,marching in his great strength?\u201CIt
        is I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, announcing your salvation!It is I,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, who has the power to save!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Why are your clothes so red,as if you have been treading out grapes?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI have been treading the winepress alone;no one was there to
        help me.In my anger I have trampled my enemiesas if they were grapes.In my
        fury I have trampled my foes.Their blood has stained my clothes.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the time has come for me to avenge my people,to ransom them from
        their oppressors.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I was amazed to see that no one intervenedto help the oppressed.So
        I myself stepped in to save them with my strong arm,and my wrath sustained
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Praise for Deliverance
      content: "I crushed the nations in my angerand made them stagger and fall to
        the ground,spilling their blood upon the earth.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will tell of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s unfailing love.I
        will praise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> for all he has done.I will rejoice
        in his great goodness to Israel,which he has granted according to his mercy
        and love.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He said, \u201CThey are my very own people.Surely they will not betray
        me again.\u201DAnd he became their Savior.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In all their suffering he also suffered,and he personally[[COMMENT(0)]]
        rescued them.In his love and mercy he redeemed them.He lifted them up and
        carried themthrough all the years.  '
      comments:
      - number: '63:9 '
        content: Hebrew <b>and the angel of his presence.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'But they rebelled against himand grieved his Holy Spirit.So he became
        their enemyand fought against them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then they remembered those days of oldwhen Moses led his people out
        of Egypt.They cried out, \u201CWhere is the one who brought Israel through
        the sea,with Moses as their shepherd?Where is the one who sent his Holy Spiritto
        be among his people?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Where is the one whose power was displayedwhen Moses lifted up his
        hand\u2014the one who divided the sea before them,making himself famous forever?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Where is the one who led them through the bottom of the sea?They
        were like fine stallionsracing through the desert, never stumbling.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Prayer for Mercy and Pardon
      content: "As with cattle going down into a peaceful valley,the Spirit of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave them rest.You led your people, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and
        gained a magnificent reputation.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: '  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, look down from heaven;look from your
        holy, glorious home, and see us.Where is the passion and the mightyou used
        to show on our behalf?Where are your mercy and compassion now?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Surely you are still our Father!Even if Abraham and Jacob[[COMMENT(0)]]
        would disown us,  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, you would still be our Father.You
        are our Redeemer from ages past.  '
      comments:
      - number: '63:16 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Israel. </b>See note on 14:1.
    - title: 
      content: '  <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, why have you allowed us to turn from
        your path?Why have you given us stubborn hearts so we no longer fear you?Return
        and help us, for we are your servants,the tribes that are your special possession.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'How briefly your holy people possessed your holy place,and now our
        enemies have destroyed it.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '    [[COMMENT(0)]]Oh, that you would burst from the heavens and come
        down!How the mountains would quake in your presence!  '
      comments:
      - number: '64:1 '
        content: '  In the Hebrew text this verse is included in 63:19.    '
    - title: 
      content: '  [[COMMENT(0)]]As fire causes wood to burnand water to boil,your
        coming would make the nations tremble.Then your enemies would learn the reason
        for your fame!  '
      comments:
      - number: '64:2 '
        content: '  Verses 64:2-12 are numbered 64:1-11 in Hebrew text.  '
    - title: 
      content: 'When you came down long ago,you did awesome deeds beyond our highest
        expectations.And oh, how the mountains quaked!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For since the world began,no ear has heardand no eye has seen a God
        like you,who works for those who wait for him!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You welcome those who gladly do good,who follow godly ways.But you
        have been very angry with us,for we are not godly.We are constant sinners;how
        can people like us be saved?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We are all infected and impure with sin.When we display our righteous
        deeds,they are nothing but filthy rags.Like autumn leaves, we wither and
        fall,and our sins sweep us away like the wind.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yet no one calls on your nameor pleads with you for mercy.Therefore,
        you have turned away from usand turned us over[[COMMENT(0)]] to our sins.  '
      comments:
      - number: '64:7 '
        content: As in Greek, Syriac, and Aramaic versions; Hebrew reads <b>melted
          us.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'And yet, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, you are our Father.We are
        the clay, and you are the potter.We all are formed by your hand.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t be so angry with us, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.Please
        don\u2019t remember our sins forever.Look at us, we pray,and see that we
        are all your people.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your holy cities are destroyed.Zion is a wilderness;yes, Jerusalem
        is a desolate ruin.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The holy and beautiful Templewhere our ancestors praised youhas been
        burned down,and all the things of beauty are destroyed.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Judgment and Final Salvation
      content: "  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says,\u201CI was ready to respond,
        but no one asked for help.I was ready to be found, but no one was looking
        for me.I said, \u2018Here I am, here I am!\u2019to a nation that did not
        call on my name.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '65:1 '
        content: Or <b>to a nation that did not bear my name.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'All day long I opened my arms to a rebellious people.[[COMMENT(0)]]But
        they follow their own evil pathsand their own crooked schemes.  '
      comments:
      - number: '65:1-2 '
        content: Greek version reads <b>I was found by people who were not looking
          for me. / I showed myself to those who were not asking for me. / All day
          long I opened my arms to them, / but they were disobedient and rebellious.
          </b>Compare Rom 10:20-21.
    - title: 
      content: 'All day long they insult me to my faceby worshiping idols in their
        sacred gardens.They burn incense on pagan altars.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'At night they go out among the graves,worshiping the dead.They eat
        the flesh of pigsand make stews with other forbidden foods.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yet they say to each other,\u2018Don\u2019t come too close or you
        will defile me!I am holier than you!\u2019These people are a stench in my
        nostrils,an acrid smell that never goes away.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CLook, my decree is written out[[COMMENT(0)]] in front of me:I
        will not stand silent;I will repay them in full!Yes, I will repay them\u2014  "
      comments:
      - number: '65:6 '
        content: Or <b>their sins are written out; </b>Hebrew reads <b>it stands
          written.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "both for their own sinsand for those of their ancestors,\u201Dsays
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CFor they also burned incense on the
        mountainsand insulted me on the hills.I will pay them back in full!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut I will not destroy them all,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CFor
        just as good grapes are found among a cluster of bad ones(and someone will
        say, \u2018Don\u2019t throw them all away\u2014some of those grapes are good!\u2019),so
        I will not destroy all Israel.For I still have true servants there.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will preserve a remnant of the people of Israel[[COMMENT(0)]]and
        of Judah to possess my land.Those I choose will inherit it,and my servants
        will live there.  '
      comments:
      - number: '65:9 '
        content: Hebrew <b>remnant of Jacob. </b>See note on 14:1.
    - title: 
      content: 'The plain of Sharon will again be filled with flocksfor my people
        who have searched for me,and the valley of Achor will be a place to pasture
        herds.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut because the rest of you have forsaken the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>and
        have forgotten his Temple,and because you have prepared feasts to honor the
        god of Fateand have offered mixed wine to the god of Destiny,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "now I will \u2018destine\u2019 you for the sword.All of you will
        bow down before the executioner.For when I called, you did not answer.When
        I spoke, you did not listen.You deliberately sinned\u2014before my very eyes\u2014and
        chose to do what you know I despise.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, this is what the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        says:\u201CMy servants will eat,but you will starve.My servants will drink,but
        you will be thirsty.My servants will rejoice,but you will be sad and ashamed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My servants will sing for joy,but you will cry in sorrow and despair.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Your name will be a curse word among my people,for the Sovereign
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will destroy youand will call his true servants
        by another name.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'All who invoke a blessing or take an oathwill do so by the God of
        truth.For I will put aside my angerand forget the evil of earlier days.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CLook! I am creating new heavens and a new earth,and no one
        will even think about the old ones anymore.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Be glad; rejoice forever in my creation!And look! I will create Jerusalem
        as a place of happiness.Her people will be a source of joy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will rejoice over Jerusalemand delight in my people.And the sound
        of weeping and cryingwill be heard in it no more.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CNo longer will babies die when only a few days old.No longer
        will adults die before they have lived a full life.No longer will people
        be considered old at one hundred!Only the cursed will die that young!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In those days people will live in the houses they buildand eat the
        fruit of their own vineyards.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Unlike the past, invaders will not take their housesand confiscate
        their vineyards.For my people will live as long as trees,and my chosen ones
        will have time to enjoy their hard-won gains.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will not work in vain,and their children will not be doomed
        to misfortune.For they are people blessed by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and
        their children, too, will be blessed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will answer them before they even call to me.While they are still
        talking about their needs,I will go ahead and answer their prayers!  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "  This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CHeaven
        is my throne,and the earth is my footstool.Could you build me a temple as
        good as that?Could you build me such a resting place?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "My hands have made both heaven and earth;they and everything in them
        are mine.[[COMMENT(0)]]I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have spoken!\u201CI
        will bless those who have humble and contrite hearts,who tremble at my word.  "
      comments:
      - number: '66:2 '
        content: As in Greek, Latin, and Syriac versions; Hebrew reads <b>these things
          are.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "But those who choose their own ways\u2014delighting in their detestable
        sins\u2014will not have their offerings accepted.When such people sacrifice
        a bull,it is no more acceptable than a human sacrifice.When they sacrifice
        a lamb,it\u2019s as though they had sacrificed a dog!When they bring an offering
        of grain,they might as well offer the blood of a pig.When they burn frankincense,it\u2019s
        as if they had blessed an idol.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will send them great trouble\u2014all the things they feared.For
        when I called, they did not answer.When I spoke, they did not listen.They
        deliberately sinned before my very eyesand chose to do what they know I despise.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Hear this message from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,all you who
        tremble at his words:\u201CYour own people hate youand throw you out for
        being loyal to my name.\u2018Let the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> be honored!\u2019
        they scoff.\u2018Be joyful in him!\u2019But they will be put to shame.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'What is all the commotion in the city?What is that terrible noise
        from the Temple?It is the voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>taking
        vengeance against his enemies.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBefore the birth pains even begin,Jerusalem gives birth to
        a son.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Who has ever seen anything as strange as this?Who ever heard of such
        a thing?Has a nation ever been born in a single day?Has a country ever come
        forth in a mere moment?But by the time Jerusalem\u2019s[[COMMENT(0)]] birth
        pains begin,her children will be born.  "
      comments:
      - number: '66:8 '
        content: "Hebrew <b>Zion\u2019s.</b>"
    - title: 
      content: "Would I ever bring this nation to the point of birthand then not
        deliver it?\u201D asks the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CNo! I would
        never keep this nation from being born,\u201Dsays your God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CRejoice with Jerusalem!Be glad with her, all you who love herand
        all you who mourn for her.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Drink deeply of her gloryeven as an infant drinks at its mother\u2019s
        comforting breasts.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says:\u201CI will give
        Jerusalem a river of peace and prosperity.The wealth of the nations will
        flow to her.Her children will be nursed at her breasts,carried in her arms,
        and held on her lap.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will comfort you there in Jerusalemas a mother comforts her child.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When you see these things, your heart will rejoice.You will flourish
        like the grass!Everyone will see the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s hand
        of blessing on his servants\u2014and his anger against his enemies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'See, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is coming with fire,and his
        swift chariots roar like a whirlwind.He will bring punishment with the fury
        of his angerand the flaming fire of his hot rebuke.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will punish the world by fireand
        by his sword.He will judge the earth,and many will be killed by him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThose who \u2018consecrate\u2019 and \u2018purify\u2019 themselves
        in a sacred garden with its idol in the center\u2014feasting on pork and
        rats and other detestable meats\u2014will come to a terrible end,\u201D says
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI can see what they are doing, and I know what they are thinking.
        So I will gather all nations and peoples together, and they will see my glory. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will perform a sign among them. And I will send those who survive
        to be messengers to the nations\u2014to Tarshish, to the Libyans[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and Lydians[[COMMENT(1)]] (who are famous as archers), to Tubal and Greece,[[COMMENT(2)]]
        and to all the lands beyond the sea that have not heard of my fame or seen
        my glory. There they will declare my glory to the nations. "
      comments:
      - number: '66:19a '
        content: As in some Greek manuscripts, which read <b>Put </b>[that is, <b>Libya</b>];
          Hebrew reads <b>Pul.</b>
      - number: '66:19b '
        content: Hebrew <b>Lud.</b>
      - number: '66:19c '
        content: Hebrew <b>Javan.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "They will bring the remnant of your people back from every nation.
        They will bring them to my holy mountain in Jerusalem as an offering to the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. They will ride on horses, in chariots and wagons,
        and on mules and camels,\u201D says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAnd I will appoint some of them to be my priests and Levites.
        I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, have spoken!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAs surely as my new heavens and earth will remain,so will you
        always be my people,with a name that will never disappear,\u201Dsays the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAll humanity will come to worship mefrom week to weekand from
        month to month.  "
      comments: []
